ADD NAME_Syzygy_Remains:0 "Syzygy Remains"
ADD WORM_CHAIN_1_title:0 "The Worm-in-Waiting: Signals"
CN2 WORM_CHAIN_1_title:0 "潜时之虫：信号"
ADD WORM_CHAIN_1_desc:0 "Something has reached out to us, from a place where time and space are shrunk to a knot.\n\nIt desires us."
CN2 WORM_CHAIN_1_desc:0 "有个未知的存在向我们打招呼，它来自一个时间与空间都坍缩成一个节点的异界。\n\n它盯上了我们。"
ADD WORM_CHAIN_2_title:0 "The Worm-in-Waiting: Signs"
CN2 WORM_CHAIN_2_title:0 "潜时之虫：征兆"
ADD WORM_CHAIN_2_desc:0 "It's unlikely that time can run both ways. It's unlikely that there's a cosmic serpent twined round the universe, gazing in with eyes bigger than our whole species. On the other hand, a number of unlikely things have happened lately."
CN2 WORM_CHAIN_2_desc:0 "时间双向流逝这种事情怎么可能会发生？一只巨大到盘踞整个宇宙的蛇形怪物正在用其巨大的双眼注视我们？这听起来就更加荒谬了。虽说最近的确发生了很多不合常理的事。"
ADD happy_with_open_loop_temple:0 "Loop Temple Visitor Center"
CN2 happy_with_open_loop_temple:0 "时循庙宇访客中心"
ADD happy_with_open_loop_temple_desc:0 "Cheery, efficient staff run guided tours past primordial sigils bright under floodlights and marked with helpful plaques."
CN2 happy_with_open_loop_temple_desc:0 "这里有热心的工作人员会带着游客参观布满灯光和标识牌的原始徽标。"
ADD spiritual_happy_with_open_loop_temple:0 "Loop Temple Pilgrims' Way"
CN2 spiritual_happy_with_open_loop_temple:0 "时循庙宇朝圣通道"
ADD spiritual_happy_with_open_loop_temple_desc:0 "Once again, the basalt arches whisper with the hushing of feet and the echo of prayers."
CN2 spiritual_happy_with_open_loop_temple_desc:0 "使用玄武岩所打造的拱形建筑再次回响起脚步的摩擦声与祈祷的低语。"
ADD waiting_world_ruins:0 "Forlorn Ruins"
CN2 waiting_world_ruins:0 "寂绝遗迹"
ADD waiting_world_ruins_desc:0 "The wind sighs in the ruins. No-one goes there."
CN2 waiting_world_ruins_desc:0 "寒风吹过荒无人烟的废墟，默默地叹息着。"
ADD d_mothballed_facilities:0 "Mothballed Facilities"
CN2 d_mothballed_facilities:0 "封存的设施"
ADD d_mothballed_facilities_desc:0 "Districts and buildings finished to the latest colonial standard, but obviously left in disuse and partial disrepair for years."
CN2 d_mothballed_facilities_desc:0 "这些区划与建筑是按照最新的殖民地标准建造的，但明显已弃置多年，并且未得到妥善维护。"
ADD loop_debris_01_object:0 "Horizon Signal Debris"
CN2 loop_debris_01_object:0 "视界信号残骸"
ADD loop_debris_02_object:0 "Spiraling Pod"
CN2 loop_debris_02_object:0 "螺旋舱"
ADD worm_quarantined:0 "Quarantined"
CN2 worm_quarantined:0 "戒备森严"
ADD worm_quarantined_desc:0 "ALL THESE WORLDS ARE YOURS - EXCEPT THIS ONE."
CN2 worm_quarantined_desc:0 "你可以占据所有的星球——唯独这个不容你染指。"
ADD worm_manifestation:0 "Peering In"
CN2 worm_manifestation:0 "凝视"
ADD worm_manifestation_desc:0 "What loops around comes around."
CN2 worm_manifestation_desc:0 "循环无始无终，终将回归原点。"
ADD tech_akx_worm_1:0 "Entropic Recursion"
CN2 tech_akx_worm_1:0 "熵递归"
ADD tech_akx_worm_1_desc:0 "The universe tends irresistibly onwards and downwards. That tendency cannot be reversed... but it can be subverted, for a price."
CN2 tech_akx_worm_1_desc:0 "宇宙总是不可抗拒地向前，也不可抗拒地向下。这个趋势看起来是不可逆转的，但若能付出相应代价，则可将其彻底颠覆。"
ADD tech_akx_worm_2:0 "Doctrine: Strange Loop"
CN2 tech_akx_worm_2:0 "学说：奇异循环"
ADD tech_akx_worm_2_desc:0 "A set of social protocols based on paradoxical intuition, and on love. When we know the System of the Loop, we learn that we can influence by receiving instructions, as well as giving them."
CN2 tech_akx_worm_2_desc:0 "这是基于相悖直觉与爱所形成的社会准则。当我们搞清了无限循环的系统之后，就会明白：遵守命令与下达命令一样，都可以造成很大的影响。"
ADD tech_akx_worm_3:0 "Omega Theory"
CN2 tech_akx_worm_3:0 "欧米伽理论"
ADD tech_akx_worm_3_desc:0 "When a temporal paradox becomes tangled, a kind of consciousness arises, with its own needs, its own desires. This is what has occurred with the consciousness that some call the Worm-in-Waiting. If we can align ourselves with that consciousness, we might just achieve a kind of immortality."
CN2 tech_akx_worm_3_desc:0 "当现时悖论变得紊乱时，便会产生某种意识，它会拥有自己的需求与渴求。所谓的“潜时之虫”就是如此的案例。如果能够跟这种意识保持一致，那我们相当于获得了永生。"
ADD TECH_UNLOCK_AKX_WORM_3_TITLE:0 "$tech_akx_worm_3$"
CN2 TECH_UNLOCK_AKX_WORM_3_TITLE:0 "$tech_akx_worm_3$"
ADD TECH_UNLOCK_AKX_WORM_3_DESC:0 "$tech_akx_worm_3_desc$"
CN2 TECH_UNLOCK_AKX_WORM_3_DESC:0 "$tech_akx_worm_3_desc$"
ADD tech_akx_worm_partial_custom:0 "§HFuture Glimpse:§! $tech_akx_worm_3$"
CN2 tech_akx_worm_partial_custom:0 "§H未来一瞥：§!$tech_akx_worm_3$"
ADD tech_akx_worm_partial_custom_desc:0 "An inkling of coming perspectives and past affections.\n\nHalf of a whole, useless on its own; when complete may allow our scientists to stumble upon the §H$tech_akx_worm_3$§! technology."
CN2 tech_akx_worm_partial_custom_desc:0 "关于未来与过去的模糊迹象。\n\n这两部分景象各自都没有任何用处，但是一旦合并起来将可以允许我们的科学家们进一步推进§H$tech_akx_worm_3$§!科技突破。"
ADD building_akx_worm_1:0 "Spiral-Feed Power Hub"
CN2 building_akx_worm_1:0 "螺旋传输电力中心"
ADD building_akx_worm_1_desc:0 "Significantly increases the power output of the planet using techniques with no place in conventional physics. Implicated in night-terrors and dreams of falling."
CN2 building_akx_worm_1_desc:0 "使用颠覆传统物理学的新技术来大幅提高能源产出。此技术跟梦魇和坠落梦境有关。"
ADD building_akx_worm_2:0 "Loop Institute"
CN2 building_akx_worm_2:0 "无限循环学院"
ADD building_akx_worm_2_desc:0 "Loop teachings encourage intuition, compliance and a valuable sense of perspective."
CN2 building_akx_worm_2_desc:0 "无限循环教育十分注重对直觉、服从力与洞察力的培养。"
ADD building_akx_worm_3:0 "Omega Alignment"
CN2 building_akx_worm_3:0 "欧米伽排列"
ADD building_akx_worm_3_desc:0 "The surface of this object angles space. The interior is not visible to any sensor or imaging technology available. But we all know what's in there."
CN2 building_akx_worm_3_desc:0 "这个物体的表面可以扭曲空间。无论使用何种传感器或者成像技术都无法探测到其内部，虽说我们都很清楚里面有着什么东西。"
ADD requires_power_hub_absence:1 "§RThe presence of any $building_power_hub_1$ or $building_power_hub_2$ on the planet will disturb the delicate helical flows that are integral to the proper functioning of the Spiral-Feed Power Hub.§!"
CN2 requires_power_hub_absence:1 "§R星球若有任何$building_power_hub_1$或者$building_power_hub_2$存在，都将干扰纤弱的螺旋浮流，使螺旋传输电力中心无法运行。§!"
ADD building_worm_mine:0 "Spiral-Hewn Mine"
CN2 building_worm_mine:0 "螺旋切削矿井"
ADD building_worm_mine_desc:0 "Narrow shafts twist around spiraling mineral veins."
CN2 building_worm_mine_desc:0 "在螺旋状的矿脉周围，围绕着一条条狭窄的矿道。"
ADD building_worm_farm:0 "Loop-Plowed Farm"
CN2 building_worm_farm:0 "循环开垦农场"
ADD building_worm_farm_desc:0 "The food crops lean into the wind, somehow."
CN2 building_worm_farm_desc:0 "这里的作物不知为何都是向着风吹的方向生长。"
ADD leader_trait_foredoomed_to_a_rendezvous:2 "Foredoomed to a Rendezvous"
CN2 leader_trait_foredoomed_to_a_rendezvous:2 "注定相遇"
ADD leader_trait_foredoomed_to_a_rendezvous_desc:2 "Experienced a troubling future."
CN2 leader_trait_foredoomed_to_a_rendezvous_desc:2 "经历了一段令人不安的未来。"
ADD HORIZON_SIGNAL_PROJECT:0 "Analyze the Horizon Signal"
CN2 HORIZON_SIGNAL_PROJECT:0 "分析视界信号"
ADD HORIZON_SIGNAL_PROJECT_DESC:0 "Dedicate a science vessel to deciphering the unlikely signal from the black hole in the [Root.GetStarName] system."
CN2 HORIZON_SIGNAL_PROJECT_DESC:0 "派一艘科研船对 [Root.GetStarName] 黑洞发出的神秘信号进行解密。"
ADD LOOP_TEMPLE_PROJECT:0 "Investigate the Loop Temple"
CN2 LOOP_TEMPLE_PROJECT:0 "调查无限时循庙宇"
ADD LOOP_TEMPLE_PROJECT_DESC:0 "Establish a research project to learn more about the Loop Temple, its origins, and its purpose."
CN2 LOOP_TEMPLE_PROJECT_DESC:0 "创立研究项目，对无限时循庙宇的起源与其作用进行调查。"
ADD MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_1:0 "Study the Messenger, and its message"
CN2 MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_1:0 "研究遗矢族，与其传递的讯息。"
ADD MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_1_DESC:0 "Perhaps we can establish a connection to certain other events - perhaps even find an explanation."
CN2 MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_1_DESC:0 "也许可以把当前的这个现象跟其他事件联系起来——搞不好就能从中找出真相。"
ADD MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_UNLEASHED:0 "Study the Messenger connection"
CN2 MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_UNLEASHED:0 "研究遗矢族关系"
ADD MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_UNLEASHED_DESC:0 "Initial findings suggest that it was a more intelligent although, perhaps, feebler form."
CN2 MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_UNLEASHED_DESC:0 "初步调查结果显示，该种群比我们智慧更高，但体质似乎更为瘦弱。"
ADD MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_LEASHED:0 "Study the Messenger connection"
CN2 MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_LEASHED:0 "研究遗矢族关系"
ADD MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_LEASHED_DESC:0 "Initial findings suggest that it was a much more rugged and, perhaps, more aggressive form."
CN2 MESSENGER_POD_PROJECT_2_LEASHED_DESC:0 "初步调查结果显示，该种群比我们更为壮硕，攻击意愿也更强。"
ADD COILS_GOD_PROJECT_DISRUPT:0 "Disrupt the Coils rituals"
CN2 COILS_GOD_PROJECT_DISRUPT:0 "破坏聚集仪式。"
ADD COILS_GOD_PROJECT_DISRUPT_DESC:0 "Interference, sabotage, disinformation. We'll do as much as we can without crossing the line."
CN2 COILS_GOD_PROJECT_DISRUPT_DESC:0 "用信号干涉也好，用蛮力破坏也罢，用假情报误导也可以，反正不要做得太过火就行。"
ADD COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PREVENT:0 "Prevent the Coils rituals"
CN2 COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PREVENT:0 "阻止聚集仪式"
ADD COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PREVENT_DESC:0 "Covert operations including forgery, kidnapping, indoctrination, even arson and murder: we do what we must."
CN2 COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PREVENT_DESC:0 "假造也好，绑架也罢，洗脑也行，就算戕害他人以及造成财产损失我们也在所不惜，反正一定要全力施为。"
ADD COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PARTICIPATE:0 "Participate in the Coils rituals"
CN2 COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PARTICIPATE:0 "参与聚集仪式"
ADD COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PARTICIPATE_DESC:0 "Send ethnographers to the surface to watch the Coils rituals up close. This is a remarkable cultural event! We must learn as much as we can."
CN2 COILS_GOD_PROJECT_PARTICIPATE_DESC:0 "派种群学家到星球表面，近距离观察聚集仪式。这是一个了不得的文化活动，我们必须尽量仔细去考察。"
ADD WAITING_WORLD_DISAPPEARANCE:0 "Investigate the disappearance of the population"
CN2 WAITING_WORLD_DISAPPEARANCE:0 "调查人员消失事件"
ADD WAITING_WORLD_DISAPPEARANCE_DESC:0 "There were too many colonists, and now there are none at all. What happened?"
CN2 WAITING_WORLD_DISAPPEARANCE_DESC:0 "之前是殖民者多得不正常，现在却是全都失踪了。这是怎么回事？"
ADD WAITING_WORLD_HYPERAPPEARANCE:0 "Investigate the... whatever happened to the population"
CN2 WAITING_WORLD_HYPERAPPEARANCE:0 "调查一下……当地人口到底出了什么问题。"
ADD WAITING_WORLD_HYPERAPPEARANCE_DESC:0 "There were too many colonists, and now there seems to be a completely different population. What happened?"
CN2 WAITING_WORLD_HYPERAPPEARANCE_DESC:0 "之前是殖民者多得不正常，现在是殖民者全都变成了别的种群。这是怎么回事？"
ADD WAITING_WORLD_PURGE:0 "Purge the population of presumed alien duplicates"
CN2 WAITING_WORLD_PURGE:0 "清除殖民地内所有疑似外星人伪装成的人口"
ADD WAITING_WORLD_PURGE_DESC:0 "The only way to deal with the mysterious population replacement on [Root.GetName] is to enact an orbital bombardment regime which will purge them all."
CN2 WAITING_WORLD_PURGE_DESC:0 "解决 [Root.GetName] 上人口被掉包的唯一办法，就是对其进行彻底的轨道轰炸，将当地人口清除一空。"
ADD WORM_ENTRY_POINT:0 "Generate the Entry Point"
CN2 WORM_ENTRY_POINT:0 "产生入口"
ADD WORM_ENTRY_POINT_DESC:0 "The Theory suggests that the temporal anomalies we have encountered are the cause of the thing we call the Loop, or the Worm. It's a tangled knot of paradoxes that has become conscious; a nexus of awareness and desire outside time. Its cause, or its result - it's hard to say with something like this. But it is attracted to endings and to beginnings. We can use the Omega Alignment to bring it through to our home system. If we do, something will certainly happen. This is many things, but especially, it is science."
CN2 WORM_ENTRY_POINT_DESC:0 "根据欧米伽理论，被我们称为无限循环，即时之虫的东西，正是时间异常所生产出来的。它是由纠结在一起的悖论所产生的意识；它是游离于时间之外的意识与渴求的结合体。它的成因与后果都无法被估测。不过它很明显对结束与开始非常感兴趣。我们可以使用欧米伽排列将它传送到我们的母星星系。这么做肯定会引发未知后果。此物从不同的角度去看可以看出千百种结论，但有一点是毫无疑问的，它就是科学。"
ADD HORIZON_DEBRIS_PROJECT:0 "Investigate fragments at Horizon Signal origin"
CN2 HORIZON_DEBRIS_PROJECT:0 "调查视界信号来源处的碎片"
ADD HORIZON_DEBRIS_PROJECT_DESC:0 "When the drive detonated, it interrupted the changes in space around the ship. The fragments exhibit unusual physical and temporal properties."
CN2 HORIZON_DEBRIS_PROJECT_DESC:0 "引擎被引爆时，飞船周围的空间变化受到了干扰。它的碎片显示出了超乎寻常的物理与时间属性。"
ADD SYZYGY_DEBRIS_PROJECT:0 "Investigate the remains of the "Syzygy""
CN2 SYZYGY_DEBRIS_PROJECT:0 "调查朔望号遗骸"
ADD SYZYGY_DEBRIS_PROJECT_DESC:0 "The "Syzygy" had spent time in another place. A possible future? An alternate universe? We can learn more."
CN2 SYZYGY_DEBRIS_PROJECT_DESC:0 "朔望号在一个未知的空间停留过一段时间。那里到底是未来？还是一个平行宇宙？这很有研究的价值。"
ADD akx.9000.name:0 "The Horizon Signal"
CN2 akx.9000.name:0 "视界信号"
ADD akx.9000.desc:0 "An alert communications officer has identified what appears to be a faint signal, almost lost in the gamma-ray flashes from the black hole here - faint, but unmistakably artificial. This raises intriguing possibilities for our scientists."
CN2 akx.9000.desc:0 "一位警报通信官发现了一道十分微弱的信号，它在黑洞所产生的伽马射线覆盖下几乎完全被淹没了——此信号虽然微弱，却毫无疑问它并非天然产生的。我们的科学家对此发现产生了许多有趣的猜测。"
ADD akx.9001.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: §HGRAVITY IS DESIRE§!"
CN2 akx.9001.name:0 "视界信号：§H引力即渴求§!"
ADD akx.9001.desc:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] reports that the signal was unexpectedly easy to decipher... but their team has spent considerable time confirming that it's not a hoax. It is a repeating, half-coherent message in the [Root.Owner.GetAdj] language - something like a poem. It repeats the phrases §HGRAVITY IS DESIRE§! and §HTIME IS SIGHT§!. It encodes co-ordinates near the black hole. And it ends with a dedication §Gby name§! to the Science Officer - who adds dispassionately that they have confirmed that the signal has been radiating into interstellar space since before their birth. In fact, the signal may predate our civilization."
CN2 akx.9001.desc:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 回报称，信号的解密出乎意料的简单……但他的团队还是花了大量时间才最终确定它的真实性。信号的内容是不断重复的不通顺的 [Root.Owner.GetAdj] 语语句——乍看之下感觉有点像是诗歌。内容是重复的语句：§H引力即渴求§!和§H时间即眼界§!。其中还包含一段被加密了的坐标，其位置是在黑洞附近。信号的最后一段则写着我们科研专员§G本人的名字§!。该科学官冷静地宣称，这个信号在我们诞生之前已经在向宇宙中传播了，有可能比我们的文明还要古老。"
ADD akx.9001.a:0 "Fascinating! Send the vessel to those co-ordinates."
CN2 akx.9001.a:0 "太神奇了！快派遣舰队前往这些坐标。"
ADD akx.a.tooltip:0 "This will begin the Horizon Signal event chain."
CN2 akx.a.tooltip:0 "此选项将开启视界信号事件链。"
ADD akx.9001.b:0 "This is a trick, or a trap. Log it and move on."
CN2 akx.9001.b:0 "这肯定是个诡诈或者陷阱。将此发现记录在案，我们继续征途。"
ADD akx.9001.b.tooltip:0 "The techniques we developed to analyze the Signal will have some applications in Physics research."
CN2 akx.9001.b.tooltip:0 "此信号的分析技术对我们的物理学研究将会有所裨益。"
ADD akx.9005.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: §HTHE WORM§!"
CN2 akx.9005.name:0 "视界信号：§H时之虫§!"
ADD akx.9005.desc:0 "As the [Root.GetName] approaches the co-ordinates specified by the signal, it begins to report spatial distortions and curious lensing effects - a rich stream of valuable data. Then the transmission becomes distorted. What happens next is analyzed exhaustively.\n\nThe excitement in Science Officer [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName]'s voice tautens to fear as the ship's hull struggles under increasingly exotic conditions. The ship triggers a distress call. [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] cries out "the worm!" - or, perhaps, §Hthe Worm§!! Then all transmissions end. No trace of the [Root.GetName] is ever found - no further transmissions, no debris, and the space at those co-ordinates is innocuous and utterly free of distortions. But the data they sent back has advanced our Physics research dramatically. Perhaps it was worth their lives."
CN2 akx.9005.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 接近信号中提到的坐标位置后，开始探测到空间扭曲和奇怪的引力透镜效应——也为我们传回了大量宝贵的数据。随后，通讯出现干扰。至于接下来发生了什么，我们进行了全面的分析。\n\n在越发诡异的环境下，飞船外壳的状态越发严峻，科研专员 [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 语气中的激动也逐渐变成了恐惧。飞船随后发出了求救信号。 [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 大喊“是只虫！”——也有可能是在大喊§H时之虫§!！随后，所有通讯中断。 [Root.GetName] 一切存在的痕迹都消失了——再也没有进行通讯，没有发现任何残骸，坐标位置处的空间也恢复了正常，再没有出现任何扭曲或者异状。但他们传回的数据对我们的物理学研究产生了极大的推动。也许他们的牺牲还是值得的。"
ADD akx.9005.a.spiritualist:0 "Darkness; light; darkness."
CN2 akx.9005.a.spiritualist:0 "黑暗；光明；黑暗。"
ADD akx.9005.a.materialist:0 "We learn, and we go on."
CN2 akx.9005.a.materialist:0 "唯有学习，方能进步。"
ADD akx.9005.a.neutral:0 "They won't be forgotten."
CN2 akx.9005.a.neutral:0 "我们会铭记他们的牺牲的。"
ADD akx.9006.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: - message ends -"
CN2 akx.9006.name:0 "视界信号：-信息终止-"
ADD akx.9006.desc:0 "[horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] complies, with a mixture of reluctance and relief. Their psych report later indicates that they are subject to recurring nightmares - of impossible labyrinths, of the hungry vertigo of interstellar space, of their name called in the dark. Within a homeworld year, the message has ceased."
CN2 akx.9006.desc:0 " [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 带着又勉强又松了口气的心情遵照执行了。相关人员的心理报告随后表明他们在被无尽的梦魇所支配——不存在的迷宫，在无边无际的空间中伴随而来的眩晕，在黑暗中被不断地被呼唤着名字。直到一年后，这些信息才彻底消失不见。"
ADD akx.9006.a:0 "We have escaped something."
CN2 akx.9006.a:0 "我们这是逃过了一劫。"
ADD akx.9006.b:0 "We have lost something."
CN2 akx.9006.b:0 "我们这是错失了大好机会。"
ADD akx.9010.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: §HREPRISE§!"
CN2 akx.9010.name:0 "视界信号：§H重奏§!"
ADD akx.9010.desc:0 "The black hole in [horizonsignal_system.GetName] is active again. Once again, a looping signal flickers in the darkness at the edge of normal space. But this time, there's an acoustic message encoded in the signal. It sounds very like [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName]'s voice. "What was shall be," [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] intones, "what shall be was." Then the same co-ordinates as the first signal, the co-ordinates where [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] was lost - what the media has christened "the Exit Point." Then they say a name: §G[horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName]§!."
CN2 akx.9010.desc:0 " [horizonsignal_system.GetName] 的黑洞又活跃起来了。正常空间边缘处的黑暗之中，又出现了断断续续的循环信号。但这一次，在信号中夹杂着声音信息，听起来很像 [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 的声音。“过去即未来”， [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 低声吟诵道，“未来即过去。”然后是信号第一次出现的坐标位置，即 [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 失踪并被我们的媒体命名为“出口”的地方。接着，信号又传出了一个名字：§G [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] §!。"
ADD akx.9010.a.collective:0 "Send [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] to the Exit Point."
CN2 akx.9010.a.collective:0 "把 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 派到出口去。"
ADD akx.9010.a.tooltip:0 "§H[horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName]§! will arrive at the Exit Point in §Y30 days§!."
CN2 akx.9010.a.tooltip:0 "§H [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] §!将在§Y30天§!后到达出口。"
ADD akx.9010.a.collective.tooltip:0 "If they do not return, we'll remember them."
CN2 akx.9010.a.collective.tooltip:0 "如果他们一去不返的话，我们会铭记他们的牺牲的。"
ADD akx.9010.a.notcollective:0 "[horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] volunteers to go. Permit it."
CN2 akx.9010.a.notcollective:0 " [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 自愿前往。批准。"
ADD akx.9010.b.collective:0 "Send them, but rig their ship's drive to detonate."
CN2 akx.9010.b.collective:0 "派他们去吧，但要给他们的飞船引擎装上造成伤害的装置。"
ADD akx.9010.b.notcollective:0 "Permit them to go, but rig their ship's drive to detonate."
CN2 akx.9010.b.notcollective:0 "允许他们前往，但要给他们的飞船引擎装上造成伤害的装置。"
ADD akx.9010.c:0 "Not this time. Ignore it."
CN2 akx.9010.c:0 "这次可不行。无视掉吧。"
ADD akx.9011.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: I'm Through"
CN2 akx.9011.name:0 "视界信号：我已通过"
ADD akx.9011.desc:0 "This time, the ship is running fully automated. [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] is the only crew-member aboard. As it approaches the Exit Point, the telemetry stream fills up with fascinating data. Once again, space flexes, gravity uncoils. [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] reads off the headline data, echoing the telemetry. They are commendably calm: we've sent a professional. It takes a little while for anyone to realize that something is peculiar about the timing.\n\n[horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] is no longer echoing the data: they're predicting it. The telemetry disagrees, but only for a few seconds, until it catches up. The monitoring team is just reporting that the prediction interval is increasing when [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] says, wonderingly: "I'm through."\n\n"It's dark," they add. "That's not a problem. We can live in the dark. I never thought of that. But of course, we can live here forever - if the Worm will only wait - "\n\nAt that moment, the signal cuts out, and the ship disappears from our team's sensors."
CN2 akx.9011.desc:0 "这一次，飞船完全靠自动控制。\n船上唯有 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 一人。随着飞船逐渐接近出口，遥感信号中渐渐填满了神奇的数据。空间折叠，引力解构的现象又一次出现了。 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 一边读取着关键数据，一边传回遥测结果。对方十分沉着冷静：我们派去的果然是一名专业人才。但过了好一会，才有人意识到时间上的古怪。\n\n [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 已不再是汇报数据了，而是在预测数据。遥测数据起初并不符合，但只过了数秒，便与预测数据完全相同了。监测团队刚刚发来汇报，预测的领先时长越来越长，正当此时，我们听到了 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 惊讶的声音：“我已通过。”\n\n“很黑。”对方还说道。“没关系，我们可以在黑暗中生存。我还真从没想过这一点。当然，我们也可以永远在这里生活下去——只要时之虫可以等下去——”\n\n就在此时，信号中断，飞船的信号也从我们团队的传感器中消失了。"
ADD akx.9011.a:0 "This is horrible."
CN2 akx.9011.a:0 "太可怕了。"
ADD akx.9011.b:0 "This is regrettable."
CN2 akx.9011.b:0 "太遗憾了。"
ADD akx.9011.c:0 "This is fascinating."
CN2 akx.9011.c:0 "太神奇了。"
ADD akx.9012.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: An Intervention"
CN2 akx.9012.name:0 "视界信号：介入"
ADD akx.9012.desc:0 "This time, [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] is the only crew-member aboard. The ship is running fully automated... and its systems are programmed to detonate the drive once conditions match those immediately prior to the last ship's disappearance. As it approaches the exit point, the telemetry stream fills up with fascinating data. Once again, space flexes, gravity uncoils. [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] reads off the headline data, echoing the telemetry. They are commendably calm: we've sent a professional. It takes a little while for anyone to realize that something is peculiar about the timing.\n\n[horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] is no longer echoing the data: They're predicting it. The telemetry disagrees, but only for a few seconds, until it catches up. Our monitoring team is just reporting that the prediction interval is increasing when there is a sudden energy spike.\n\nThe drive has detonated: a brief flare of stellar fury, quickly lost in the darkness of [horizonsignal_system.GetName]. Whatever we encountered there, it may regret its interference. We'll never know. The Horizon Signal does not come again. But our team may find something interesting in the ashes of the ship."
CN2 akx.9012.desc:0 "这次，船上仅有 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 一人。飞船完全依靠自动操控……其系统程序已设置为，根据上一次的记录，在周围环境符合上艘飞船消失时间点的状态前一瞬将飞船引擎引爆。随着飞船接近出口，遥感信号中渐渐填满了神奇的数据。空间折叠，引力解构的现象又一次出现了。 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 随时汇报着实时数据，并通过遥感进行传送。对方似乎表现了卓绝的冷静，不愧是专业人士。只不过，过了一会儿就有人发现，计时出现了奇怪的迹象。\n\n\n [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 已不再是汇报数据了，而是在预测数据。遥感数据起初并不符合，但只持续了数秒，便与预测数据完全相同了。正当监测团队在通报预测的领先时长越发变大时，突然出现了巨大的能源波动。\n\n\n引擎被引爆了：如恒星般的光芒一闪而逝，淹没在 [horizonsignal_system.GetName] 的黑暗之中。不管我们遭遇的对方是谁，应该都会后悔这次的介入。只不过，我们是无从得知了。视界信号已经不会再出现了，但我们的队伍也许能从飞船的灰烬之中找到什么有趣的东西。"
ADD akx.9012.a:0 "And yet, this may not be the end."
CN2 akx.9012.a:0 "也许，这还不算完呢。"
ADD akx.9013.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: - message ends -"
CN2 akx.9013.name:0 "视界信号：-信息终止-"
ADD akx.9013.desc:0 "[horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] complies, with obvious relief. Their psych report later indicates that they are subject to recurring nightmares - of impossible labyrinths, of the hungry vertigo of interstellar space, of their name called in the dark. Within a homeworld year, the message has ceased."
CN2 akx.9013.desc:0 " [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 明显松了口气的样子，遵照执行了。相关人员的心理报告随后表明他们在被无尽的梦魇所支配——不存在的迷宫，在无边无际的空间中伴随而来的眩晕，在黑暗中被不断地被呼唤着名字。一年后，这些信息才彻底消失不见。"
ADD akx.9013.a:0 "A missed opportunity."
CN2 akx.9013.a:0 "我们这是错失了大好机会。"
ADD akx.9013.b:0 "A narrow escape."
CN2 akx.9013.b:0 "九死一生啊。"
ADD akx.9020.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: §HTHE TRINE THE QUINE THE TRINE§!"
CN2 akx.9020.name:0 "视界信号：§H自生的三神§!"
ADD akx.9020.desc:0 "Once again, the Horizon Signal in [horizonsignal_system.GetName] is active. It has upped its game. Once again, the transmission includes the Exit Point's co-ordinates. It's signed with the private comm keys of [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] and [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName]. But this time, it's a generative text program written in an elderly programming language that creates what appear to be love poems - love poems directed to [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName].\n\nThey're honestly not very good love poems. But it is, our scientists agree, quite difficult to generate love poems procedurally, and quite unusual for a black hole to send love poems at all."
CN2 akx.9020.desc:0 " [horizonsignal_system.GetName] 的视界信号又启动了。这次势头更劲。这次的传讯中依旧包含出口的坐标，并以 [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 和 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 的私人通讯识别码署名。但是通讯的内容是一段老式编程语言，运行后会自动生成一段情诗——而这情诗，是指名写给 [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 的。\n\n\n诗写得并不是十分优美，但我们的科学家一致承认，想要像这样自动按步骤生成情诗是十分困难的，而黑洞本身会发出情诗这种事，本身就已经够匪夷所思了。"
ADD akx.9020.a:0 "Well, it's asked nicely. Send [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName]."
CN2 akx.9020.a:0 "嗯，对方既然这么有礼，那就把 [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 派过去吧。"
ADD akx.9020.a.tooltip:0 "§H[horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName]§! will arrive at the Exit Point in §Y30 days§!."
CN2 akx.9020.a.tooltip:0 "§H [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] §!将在§Y30天后§!到达出口。"
ADD akx.9020.b:0 "Send [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName], with their drive rigged to blow."
CN2 akx.9020.b:0 "派 [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 去吧，别忘了给他们的引擎装上造成伤害的装置。"
ADD akx.9020.c:0 "This is sinister, and ridiculous, and sinister. Let it go."
CN2 akx.9020.c:0 "这不仅是不祥，简直是愚傻又不祥。算了吧。"
ADD akx.9021.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: Where the End Comes From"
CN2 akx.9021.name:0 "视界信号：终末的来处"
ADD akx.9021.desc:0 ""This will be the end of me," [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] says at the briefing before launch. "I know I won't come back. But I think I always knew this would happen. Whatever is in the hole has been waiting for us for a long long time - I think it's been waiting for me, since before I was born."\n\nOnce again, the single-pilot ship approaches the Exit Point. Once again, space boils like a fever. Again, our sensor arrays soak up fascinating data. This time, [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] is silent. The telemetry becomes intermittent; and then it, too, is silent. The ship has reached the Exit Point. The conditions around it are returning to normal. Nothing has happened.\n\nNothing? The monitoring team mutter furiously. The ship is different... in fact, it's a different ship. It's [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName]'s vessel, lost these years past, drifting now away from the Exit Point. A salvage team finds it pristine and empty - no trace of crew, and no sign of violence. But there's a journal entry in [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName]'s name, titled §HWHAT WAS WILL BE§!. Our scientists review it nervously. "Impossible," one says. "I hope so," says another.\n\nThe ship is renamed the "Foundling" and returned to service. The Signal, dead or sleeping, says nothing at all, ever again."
CN2 akx.9021.desc:0 "“我这次是回不来了，” [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 在出发前的简报中说道，“我知道我回不来的。但我早就预料到这种事会发生。那黑洞的里面的东西已经等了我们很久了——我感觉，早在我出生之前，他们就在等我了。”\n\n再一次，只载有一名人员的飞船接近了出口。再一次，空间如同沸腾一般扭曲起来。再一次，我们的传感器列阵传回了不可思议的数据。但这一次， [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 却十分沉寂。遥感信号变得断断续续，随后，也归于沉寂。飞船到达了出口。周围的环境回归了正常。却什么也没发生。\n\n什么也没发生？监测团队气愤地低语着。但飞船却变化了……其实，我们观测的已经是另一艘船了。我们发现的是 [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 的飞船，在消失了这么多年之后，现在却从出口处缓缓飘了出来。派出的回收队伍发现飞船完好无损，但是空无一物——乘员都消失了，也没有打斗的痕迹。但却留下了一篇 [horizonsignal_firstleader.GetName] 署名的日志，标题为§H过去即未来§!。我们的科学家紧张地对其进行了调查。“这不可能。”一位科学家说道。另一位则回应：“但愿不可能吧。”\n\n飞船被重新命名为“浪子号”并回归了队伍。不知信号是陷入了睡眠，还是已经彻底死亡，总之再也没有出现。"
ADD akx.9021.a:0 "And yet, this may not be the end."
CN2 akx.9021.a:0 "也许，这还不算完呢。"
ADD akx.9022.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: An Intervention"
CN2 akx.9022.name:0 "视界信号：介入"
ADD akx.9022.desc:0 ""This will be the end of me," they say at the briefing before launch. "I know I won't come back. But I think I always knew this would happen. Whatever is in the hole has been waiting for us for a long, long time - I think it's been waiting for me, since before I was born."\n\nOnce again, the single-pilot ship approaches the Exit Point. Once again, space boils like a fever. Again, our sensor arrays soak up fascinating data. This time, [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] is silent. The telemetry becomes intermittent...\n\nAnd then the drive detonates: a brief flare of stellar fury, quickly lost in the darkness of the [horizonsignal_system.GetName] system. Whatever we encountered there, it may regret its interference. We'll never know. The Horizon Signal does not come again. But our team may find something interesting in the ashes of the ship."
CN2 akx.9022.desc:0 "“我这次是回不来了，”他们在出发前的简报中说道，“我知道我回不来的。但我早就预料到这种事会发生。那黑洞的里面的东西已经等了我们很久了——我感觉，早在我出生之前，他们就在等我了。”\n\n再一次，只载有一名驾驶员的飞船接近了出口。再一次，空间如同沸腾一般扭曲起来。再一次，我们的传感器列阵传回了不可思议的数据。但这一次， [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 却十分沉寂。遥感信号变得断断续续……\n\n引擎被引爆了：如恒星般的光芒一闪而逝，淹没在 [horizonsignal_system.GetName] 的黑暗之中。不管我们遭遇的对方是谁，应该都会对这次的插手感到后悔不已吧。只不过，我们是无从得知了。视界信号已经不会再出现了，但我们的队伍也许能从飞船的灰烬之中找到什么有趣的东西。"
ADD akx.9022.a:0 "And yet, this may not be the end."
CN2 akx.9022.a:0 "也许，这还不算完呢。"
ADD akx.9023.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: - message ends -"
CN2 akx.9023.name:0 "视界信号：-信息终止-"
ADD akx.9023.desc:0 "[horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] complies, with obvious relief. Their psych report later indicates that they are subject to recurring nightmares - of impossible labyrinths, of the hungry vertigo of interstellar space, of their name called in the dark. Within a homeworld year, the message has ceased."
CN2 akx.9023.desc:0 " [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 明显松了口气的样子，遵照执行了。相关人员的心理报告随后表明他们在被无尽的梦魇所支配——不存在的迷宫，在无边无际的空间中伴随而来的眩晕，在黑暗中被不断地被呼唤着名字。一年后，这些信息才彻底消失不见。"
ADD akx.9090.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: Cause and Effect"
CN2 akx.9090.name:0 "视界信号：因与果"
ADD akx.9090.desc:0 "Our observers report that the talkative black hole in [horizonsignal_system.GetName] became briefly active around the time of [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName]'s death. A rapid and unintelligible signal burst. Like a fit of rage, one of the more imaginative observers adds."
CN2 akx.9090.desc:0 "我们的观测站发现 [horizonsignal_system.GetName] 中发送信号的黑洞在 [horizonsignal_secondleader.GetName] 死亡时短暂进入了活跃状态，发出了一道短暂且无法解读的信号波。一位想象力丰富的观测员补充称，信号如同怒气彰显一般。"
ADD akx.9090.a:0 "This isn't over."
CN2 akx.9090.a:0 "这还不算完呢。"
ADD akx.9091.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: In Memoriam"
CN2 akx.9091.name:0 "视界信号：纪念"
ADD akx.9091.desc:0 "Our observers report that the talkative black hole in [horizonsignal_system.GetName] became briefly active around the time of [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName]'s death. It's transmitted the original poem-program again, three times. Like, one of our more whimsically inclined observers adds, a drunken mourner singing at a wake."
CN2 akx.9091.desc:0 "我们的观测站发现 [horizonsignal_system.GetName] 中发送信号的黑洞在 [horizonsignal_thirdleader.GetName] 死亡时短暂进入了活跃状态，将最初的诗歌信号重新发送了三次。一位异想天开的观测员称，这有点像醉酒的死者亲朋在守丧时放声高歌。"
ADD akx.9091.a:0 "This isn't over."
CN2 akx.9091.a:0 "这还不算完呢。"
ADD akx.9095.name:0 "The Horizon Signal: A Lesson in the Ashes"
CN2 akx.9095.name:0 "视界信号：灰烬中的启示"
ADD akx.9095.desc:0 "We've reproduced conditions that approximate those around the black hole. We've found that the fragments we recover cycle between states, in ways that should be impossible - as if time were oscillating. We can derive energy from this - although there are worrying changes to local spacetime."
CN2 akx.9095.desc:0 "我们成功模拟了黑洞附近的环境状况，并发现碎片在该环境中会在数个状态间循环，然而，这种循环在理论上是不可能的——简直如同时间本身在震荡一般。我们可以从中获取能源，但有人担忧这会对当地的时空造成改变。"
ADD akx.9100.name:0 "The Loop Temple: Signs in the Stone"
CN2 akx.9100.name:0 "时循庙宇：石之印"
ADD akx.9100.desc:0 "Archaeologists have found a forgotten temple in the remote highlands of [Root.GetName] - buried for centuries, but recently exposed by an earthquake. Dating techniques suggest it's a pre-industrial relic, hand-hewn from volcanic rock. However, the recurring symbol on the walls and radial altar - a Möbius-looped serpent consuming its own tail - has no obvious precedent in our early history, and the inscriptions use an unknown alphabet. One excitable archaeologist suggests it's a relic left by an unknown precursor race.\n\nIn a presumably meaningless coincidence, the quake seems to have occurred at the same time as the final message from the black hole in [horizonsignal_system.GetName]."
CN2 akx.9100.desc:0 "考古学家在 [Root.GetName] 的偏远高原发现了一栋失落的庙宇——它已经在地下掩埋了数百年，但一次地震使其终得再见天日。年代测定技术表明，它是工业文明前的文物，是使用火山岩手工雕刻形成的产物。然而，墙上与放射状圣坛上反复出现的莫比乌斯环图形，在我们的早期历史中却没有任何记载，而且雕刻的铭文使用的是我们前所未见的字母。一位考古学家激动地说，这可能是某个未知先驱种群留下的文物。\n\n\n不知是不是毫无关联的巧合，地震似乎是在 [horizonsignal_system.GetName] 的黑洞发出最后一条信息的同时发生的。"
ADD akx.9100.spiritual.a:0 "A way has been opened for us."
CN2 akx.9100.spiritual.a:0 "这是为我们打开了新的道路啊。"
ADD akx.9100.neutral.a:0 "This merits study."
CN2 akx.9100.neutral.a:0 "这值得研究。"
ADD akx.9100.b:0 "Ominous."
CN2 akx.9100.b:0 "真是不祥之兆。"
ADD akx.9101.name:0 "The Loop Temple: Time and Stone"
CN2 akx.9101.name:0 "时循庙宇：时与石"
ADD akx.9101.desc:0 "Our scientists have learned a great deal about the subterranean temple, but some questions remain. A roof aperture - along with the radial altar - suggests it was once a solar calendar, but it's so badly damaged by the earthquake that we can't be certain. If the builders found any particular dates important, we'll never know which ones. We've had better luck with the "unknown alphabet." It's a debased variant of a better-known hieratic script - not an alien language at all - and we've successfully deciphered it.\n\nThe temple is dedicated to the "Waiting Worm" or the §HWorm-in-Waiting§!. Most of the inscriptions are sonorous, poetic invocations requesting its appearance or - if read in the other direction - its departure. There is also a body of inscriptions describing the "operations of the universe," which our more excitable archaeologist swears contains references to advanced field equations - nothing new to us, but very impressive for a temple of this vintage. We have yet to find a physicist who's prepared to go on record in agreeing that the references are meaningful, though.\n\nThe temple holds no cosmic secrets or alien weapons, as far as we can tell, but its dark spaces have a distinctive, menacing beauty - and the poetry of the invocations to the Worm-in-Waiting becomes fashionable. They are set to popular music; they are published in collections."
CN2 akx.9101.desc:0 "我们的科学家已经对这栋地下庙宇进行了较为详尽的研究与了解，但还是有几个疑问没有解开。屋顶上的光圈与地面的放射状圣坛，均表明这曾是一个日晷结构；但由于地震造成的严重结构损坏，我们也不敢如此定论。如果当时的建造者着重突出了某个重要的日期，如今也已不可考了。相比之下，我们对于“未知字母”的研究还算成果喜人。研究表明，这其实是基于一种较为出名的由僧侣使用的文字，稍加改动而成的。这种原文字本身就是我们文明的产物，我们现已将这种未知语言完全破解。这座庙供奉的是§H“潜时之虫”§!。刻文的大部分都是诗句般的祷词，内容大致为祈求潜时之虫的降临，但如果反着阅读，则可翻译为祈求潜时之虫的离去。还有一段刻文描述了“宇宙的运作”，我们的考古学家激动地表示，这其中定然包含对于高端场方程的描述——我们对这一技术并不陌生，但考虑到这座庙的年代久远，就不可谓不惊人了。但是，目前我们尚未发现有哪位科学家对这些刻文中的阐述公然表示认同。\n\n据我们观察，神庙中没有包藏任何宇宙秘密或外星武器。但其黑暗的空间有一种独特鲜明又充满威胁感的美，而献给潜时之虫的诗歌祷词也成为了时尚，被写入了流行音乐，并被编成合集进行发售。"
ADD akx.9101.a.notspiritual:0 "Open the Loop Temple to the public."
CN2 akx.9101.a.notspiritual:0 "将时循庙宇对公众开放。"
ADD akx.9101.a.notspiritual.tooltip:0 "Something from our past. What was, will be."
CN2 akx.9101.a.notspiritual.tooltip:0 "这来自我们的过去。过去即未来。"
ADD akx.9101.a.spiritual:0 "Make the Loop Temple a place of pilgrimage."
CN2 akx.9101.a.spiritual:0 "将时循庙宇指定为圣地。"
ADD akx.9101.a.spiritual.tooltip:0 "A wisdom from the faith of our ancestors. What was, will be. Increases planet happiness, among other things."
CN2 akx.9101.a.spiritual.tooltip:0 "这是我们祖先的智慧。过去即未来。除此之外，提高星球的幸福度。"
ADD akx.9101.b:0 "Reserve the Temple for academic study only."
CN2 akx.9101.b:0 "将庙宇保护起来，仅供学术研究使用。"
ADD akx.9101.b.tooltip:0 "Let's limit access to those who need it."
CN2 akx.9101.b.tooltip:0 "只允许必要的人接触吧。"
ADD akx.9101.c:1 "There is something wrong here. Seal the Temple."
CN2 akx.9101.c:1 "感觉有点不对劲。将庙宇彻底封印，以彰显我们的权威吧。"
ADD akx.9101.c.tooltip:0 "Better safe than sorry."
CN2 akx.9101.c.tooltip:0 "小心驶得万年船。"
ADD akx.9200.name:0 "The Messenger: §HWHAT WAS, WILL BE§!"
CN2 akx.9200.name:0 "遗矢：§H过去即未来§!"
ADD akx.9200.desc:0 "The [Root.GetName] has located a small, minimally powered artificial object, broadcasting a looping signal at local range only. These sorts of things usually turn out to be escape pods, and this looks like one of those. It's been out here a long time.\n\nWhen the crew cracks it open - carefully observing quarantine procedures - they find ancient remains, preserved by the sterile pod environment. So far, not unusual. The captain of the [Root.GetName] indicates, however, that they did not expect to find the [Root.Owner.GetAdj] words §HWHAT WAS, WILL BE; WHAT WILL BE, WAS§! daubed on the wall in the bodily fluids of the pod's occupant - who the crew are now wryly referring to as "the Messenger"". They add that there are some equally unexpected anatomical similarities between the Messenger's species, and our own."
CN2 akx.9200.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 发现了一个小型人造物体，它正以最低功率运行，在小范围内循环广播信号。这种特征的物体一般都是逃生舱，而且目前看来这个也不例外。这玩意在这里已经呆了好久了。船员严格遵循隔离程序将其打开时，发现其中的古代遗体由于舱内的无菌环境而保存完好。到目前为止，没有发现任何不寻常的现象。然而 [Root.GetName] 舰长指出，他们没有想到在舱内会有用这些生物的迷之体液写下的 [Root.Owner.GetAdj] 单词：§H过去即未来，未来即过去§!——船员现在开始用“遗矢族”来称呼这种生物了。他们还说，遗矢族种群和我们自己在解剖学上存在着异乎寻常的相似性。"
ADD akx.9201.name:0 "The Messenger: Possibilities"
CN2 akx.9201.name:0 "遗矢：可能性"
ADD akx.9201.desc:0 "We've established that the escape pod was the kind of commercially available knockoff common in the previous phase of galactic civilization - no new technologies or other insights. The remains of the Messenger, however, are another matter. It's unmistakably an ancestor or a variant of the [Root.Owner.GetAdj] species. Perhaps we have cousins out there - or perhaps we were subject to genetic manipulation by a precursor race. [researchingscientist.GetName] is requesting permission to conduct more extensive research."
CN2 akx.9201.desc:0 "我们已经查明，这个逃生舱是上个银河文明时期的产物，属于量产商用型——并没有可以利用的创新手段与科技。然而，遗矢族的遗体却为我们带来了惊人的发现。有确凿证据表明，他们是 [Root.Owner.GetAdj] 种群的祖先。也许我们在宇宙中还有旁系的兄弟——甚至连我们都可能是先驱种群进行基因改造的产物。 [researchingscientist.GetName] 正申请进行进一步的研究。"
ADD akx.9201.militarist.a:0 "Give permission to continue."
CN2 akx.9201.militarist.a:0 "允许继续进行。"
ADD akx.9201.militarist.a.tooltip:0 "Increases Genome Mapping research"
CN2 akx.9201.militarist.a.tooltip:0 "增加基因组图谱研究"
ADD akx.9201.notmilitarist.b:0 "Release the funding."
CN2 akx.9201.notmilitarist.b:0 "提供资金。"
ADD akx.9201.notmilitarist.b.tooltip:0 "Increases Genome Mapping research by [moderate amount]"
CN2 akx.9201.notmilitarist.b.tooltip:0 "基因图谱研究提升 [moderate amount] "
ADD akx.9201.c:0 "No. And [researchingscientist.GetName] must release their existing research."
CN2 akx.9201.c:0 "不行。不仅如此， [researchingscientist.GetName] 还必须交出所有现存的研究成果。"
ADD akx.9201.c.tooltip:0 "There are some things it's better not to know."
CN2 akx.9201.c.tooltip:0 "有些事情还是不要知道比较好。"
ADD akx.9210.name:0 "The Messenger: Unleashed"
CN2 akx.9210.name:0 "遗矢：释放"
ADD akx.9210.desc:0 "[researchingscientist.GetName] has reconstructed the Messenger species. It's feebler than ours, but has significantly improved cognitive abilities. There is some confusion about whether we were the source species, and the Messenger the modified version, or whether the Messenger was our ancestor. It is a little embarrassing to imagine that we might be descended from such an effete species - but [researchingscientist.GetName] is firmly of that opinion. Indeed, they consider the loss of cognitive abilities a "tragedy."\n\nSuch a tragedy that they have undergone a retroviral treatment to alter their own physiology to that of the Messengers. They insist that this will equip them much better to continue the project."
CN2 akx.9210.desc:0 " [researchingscientist.GetName] 已经成功重建了遗矢族种群。他们的体质比我们虚弱，但认知能力显然比我们高上许多。至于我们两个种群谁是原始种群，谁是后来的改进版本，目前尚不明确。但是想想我们是这种瘦弱种群的后代，就会禁不住感到尴尬——但 [researchingscientist.GetName] 似乎却言之凿凿。说起来，这位科学家认为，我们认知能力的退化可称得上是“种群的大悲剧”。\n\n有些研究人员甚至为此接受逆转录基因治疗，将自己的体质改造成了遗矢族的特征。他们还坚持认为，这对研究的继续进行具有重大意义。"
ADD akx.9210.a:0 "A creative form of treason! Execute them, please."
CN2 akx.9210.a:0 "这是变相的对帝国不忠行为！请立刻消灭他们。"
ADD akx.9210.b:0 "A creative form of treason! Execute them, please. Destroy their notes."
CN2 akx.9210.b:0 "这是变相的对帝国不忠行为！请立刻消灭他们，并销毁研究成果。"
ADD akx.9210.c:0 "Excellent idea! Get on with it, then."
CN2 akx.9210.c:0 "好主意！就这么去做吧。"
ADD akx.9211.name:0 "The Messenger: A New Light"
CN2 akx.9211.name:0 "遗矢：新的光明"
ADD akx.9211.desc:0 "[researchingscientist.GetName] has now recreated the genetic heritage of the Messenger species. Without stopping to ask anyone's opinion, they have also created highly contagious retroviral agent. It stalks our worlds. Under its influence, our primary species falls into a chrysalis-coma and emerges a day later as the Messenger species. This is causing, it is fair to say, some excitement."
CN2 akx.9211.desc:0 " [researchingscientist.GetName] 对遗矢族的基因构成进行了重新构造，但同时也未经允许，制作了非常容易传染的逆转录病毒。不幸的是，病毒在我方星球上迅速散布，以致星球上的主要种群人口尽数进入了蛹状昏迷状态。这种昏迷状态持续一天之后，病人就将会被完全转化为遗矢族。老实说，此状况引起了不少人的兴趣。"
ADD akx.9211.a:0 "This has gone too far. Now we end it. Control the outbreak."
CN2 akx.9211.a:0 "情况太糟糕了。一定要控制住病毒传播。"
ADD akx.9211.a.tooltip:0 "All pops on the capital planet will be converted, but there it will end."
CN2 akx.9211.a.tooltip:0 "母星所有人口都将变异，但病毒传播也将不再继续。"
ADD akx.9211.b:0 "Control the outbreak, and purge all affected citizens."
CN2 akx.9211.b:0 "控制病毒传播，消灭所有被传染的民众。"
ADD akx.9211.b.tooltip:0 "This will §RPurge all affected Pops§!: nearly the entire population of [Root.Capital.GetName]."
CN2 akx.9211.b.tooltip:0 "将会§R消灭所有被传染人口§!， [Root.Capital.GetName] 绝大部分人口将会受牵连。"
ADD akx.9211.c:0 "What was, shall be. We will change. Bring me a sample of the agent."
CN2 akx.9211.c:0 "或许我们应当抓住这次机会，进行转变。给我也来一份病毒吧。"
ADD akx.9211.c.tooltip:0 "This will transform our entire species."
CN2 akx.9211.c.tooltip:0 "整个种群都将会被转化。"
ADD akx.9220.name:0 "The Messenger: Leashed"
CN2 akx.9220.name:0 "遗矢：作茧自缚"
ADD akx.9220.desc:1 "[researchingscientist9220.GetName] has reconstructed the Messenger. It's, ah, quite impressive - worryingly so. It seems to be considerably more robust and aggressive than our current edition. There is some confusion about whether we were the source species, and the Messenger the modified version, or whether the Messenger was our ancestor. [researchingscientist9220.GetName] is firmly of the latter opinion - that we were once much more of a warrior species, and that some meddling precursor muzzled us genetically. Indeed, they consider the loss of our martial abilities a "tragedy."\n\nSuch a tragedy that they have undergone a retroviral treatment to alter their own physiology to that of the Messengers. They insist that this will equip them much better to continue the project."
CN2 akx.9220.desc:1 " [researchingscientist9220.GetName] 对信使的基因进行了重组研究。他们的确十分出色，但也令我们的科学家有些担忧。与我们现在的基因相比较，信使明显更为强健，攻击意愿也更高。现在研究人员们众说纷纭，无法确定信使到底是我们自身的进化版本，还是说他们其实是我们的祖先。 [researchingscientist9220.GetName] 本人更相信后一种说法——我们本也应当作为强大的战斗种群生活下去，却因为某个先驱文明的干涉而失去了战斗本能。据其认为，失去这种战斗能力乃是我方史上最大的“悲剧”。\n\n有些研究人员甚至为此接受逆转录基因治疗，将自己的体质改造成了信使的特征。他们还坚持认为，这对研究的继续进行具有重大意义。"
ADD akx.9220.a:0 "A creative form of treason! Execute them, please."
CN2 akx.9220.a:0 "这是变相的对帝国不忠行为！请立刻消灭他们。"
ADD akx.9220.b:0 "A creative form of treason! Execute them, please. Destroy their notes."
CN2 akx.9220.b:0 "这是变相的不忠行为！请立刻消灭他们，并将他们的研究成果销毁。"
ADD akx.9220.c:0 "Excellent idea! Get on with it, then."
CN2 akx.9220.c:0 "好主意！就这么去做吧。"
