ADD akx.9300.name:0 "A Rendezvous"
CN2 akx.9300.name:0 "太空密会"
ADD akx.9300.desc:1 "The [Root.GetName] is being hailed... by the "§HSyzygy§!" of the [Root.Owner.GetName]. This, despite the fact the "Syzygy" isn't sending any ID codes we recognize, and no ship of that name has ever been commissioned. Its commanding officer claims to be Captain §H[mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName]§!."
CN2 akx.9300.desc:1 " [Root.GetName] 收到了的问候，对方自称是 [Root.Owner.GetName] 的§H朔望号§!。然而，他们所发送来的ID号码无法识别，而我方也并没有一艘名为朔望号的飞船。这艘迷之飞船的舰长自称为 [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 。"
ADD akx.9300.a.admiralabsent:0 "Hm. Our admiral of that name is alive, well and elsewhere."
CN2 akx.9300.a.admiralabsent:0 "不对啊。咱们叫这个名字的上将现在正在别处工作。"
ADD akx.9300.a.admiralabsent.tooltip:0 "Open a channel."
CN2 akx.9300.a.admiralabsent.tooltip:0 "打开频道。"
ADD akx.9300.a.admiralpresent:0 "How interesting. [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] here."
CN2 akx.9300.a.admiralpresent:0 "还真有意思。 [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 就在这里。"
ADD akx.9300.b:0 "This *must* be an ambush. We're taking no chances. Battlestations."
CN2 akx.9300.b:0 "一定是敌人的埋伏。不能大意，做好战斗准备。"
ADD akx.9310.name:0 "A Rendezvous: the Captain that Was"
CN2 akx.9310.name:0 "太空密会：曾经的舰长"
ADD akx.9310.desc:0 "The Captain that appears on our screen is clearly [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName], but a scarred, haunted, decrepit, wrecked edition of [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName], face glossy with plasma-burns, and older - much older. The bridge in the background looks just as scarred and just as decrepit. But the Captain's voice is firm and clear.\n\n§G"FINALLY you're here. I've waited so long. My punishment is to die in battle against you. Please, end me. I'm sorry."§!"
CN2 akx.9310.desc:0 "显示屏上的舰长的的确确就是 [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] ，但比起 [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 来，似乎经历了更多风雨。他的神情中充满了迷茫、受伤与劳累，也更为年迈。他的脸上布满了各种战斗中留下的伤疤，连背景中的舰桥也历经沧桑。尽管如此，舰长的声音仍沉稳洪亮。\n\n§G“可算等到你们了。都已经忘记等了多久。给予我的惩罚就是在和你的战斗中战死。求你了，让我赶紧死个痛快吧……抱歉。”§!"
ADD akx.9310.a:0 "What's happening here? Are you really [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName]?"
CN2 akx.9310.a:0 "这到底是怎么回事？你真的是 [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 吗？"
ADD akx.9310.a.response:0 "§G"Am I? Are you the same [Root.GetSpeciesName] you were last year? Every day is a death. Every future is a choice. Time is a labyrinth, not a road."§!\n\nA chuckle. It sounds like the chuckle hurts.\n\n§G"Ask the Loop."§!"
CN2 akx.9310.a.response:0 "§G“你说我是不是？难道说你和去年此时的那个 [Root.GetSpeciesName] 也还是同一个人吗？每一天的开始就是前一天的死亡。每一个未来都需要一个抉择。时间并不是一条直线，而是无比黑暗的迷宫。”§!\n\n他勉强挤出了一丝笑容，却掩盖不住眼中的痛苦神色。\n\n§G“问问时之循环你就知道了。”§!"
ADD akx.9310.b:0 "If you want to end it, why wait? A warship is full of ways to die."
CN2 akx.9310.b:0 "如果只是想要寻死，为什么不在战舰上自行了断呢？"
ADD akx.9310.b.response:0 "§G"Don't you remember? Of course, you won't, yet - and you might not, now, not if you do it right. The Loop needs its sacrifices, and it needs them just so."§! An agonized, coughing chuckle. §G"You don't want to trifle with the Loop."§!"
CN2 akx.9310.b.response:0 "“难道你不记得了吗？也难怪，现在的你应该还没经历过。如果你这次做出正确选择的话，或许也不会有那种经历了。时之循环需要牺牲品，恰如其分的牺牲品。”他咳嗽了两声，又苦笑起来。“时之循环可不是好对付的。”"
ADD akx.9310.c:0 "What is the Loop?"
CN2 akx.9310.c:0 "时之循环到底是什么？"
ADD akx.9310.c.response:0 "§G"The Loop is what came first and what comes next - the §!§HWorm-in-Waiting§!§G - and, I suppose, the Worm is the Loop. Let's say Time is a labyrinth..."§! The Captain begins to gesture futilely.\n§G"Then the Loop is its monster. Or its maker... No, I can't explain it, and you'll know more soon. You did, in my past.\n\n"... Weapons locked?"§!"
CN2 akx.9310.c.response:0 "§G“时之循环乃是世界的起源，也是其未来——那§!§H隐藏自身的时之虫§!§G——或许那时之虫就是时之循环的本体。打个比方，时间本身就是一个迷宫”§!——舰长开始毫无章法地胡言乱语起来——§G“那时之循环就是迷宫中的怪物，不，或许是迷宫的主人？我也解释不清楚。你以后就明白了。在我的过去、你的未来中你是明白的。武器瞄准了吗？”§!"
ADD akx.9310.d.notpacifist:0 "Surrender. Whatever you've done, we can help you."
CN2 akx.9310.d.notpacifist:0 "快点投降吧。不管发生了什么，我们都会帮助你的。"
ADD akx.9310.d.notpacifist.response:0 "§G"Too late,"§! the Captain says, not without regret, and cuts the transmission."
CN2 akx.9310.d.notpacifist.response:0 "§G“已经太晚了。”§!舰长的神情变得决绝冷酷，切断了联络。"
ADD akx.9310.d.fanaticpacifist:1 "Killing is not our way. Surrender, and we'll help you."
CN2 akx.9310.d.fanaticpacifist:1 "不管是怎么一回事，好斗都不是解决问题的途径。投降吧，我们会帮你的。问题的途径。投降吧，我们会帮你的。"
ADD akx.9310.d.fanaticpacifist.response:0 "The Captain hesitates for a long time. It becomes apparent that the bridge of the "Syzygy" is empty: there are no other crew.\n\n§G"It's too late for me,"§! the Captain says at last, §G"but you're right. This is not our way. I'll do what I must."§! They cut the transmission.\n\nSensors report that the Syzygy weapons are offline; the ship is powering down. Very soon, it goes dark. When our salvage team boards the ship, they find no living creature, and no sign of the captain. But someone accessed the drive section recently; and someone overrode the safety protocols that prevented entry to the core."
CN2 akx.9310.d.fanaticpacifist.response:0 "舰长犹豫着，沉默了很久。从显示屏上可以看出，朔望号上早已灰尘满积，破败不堪，没有其他生存者了。\n\n§G“对我来说已经太晚了，”§!沉默了许久的舰长终于开了口，§G“但你说的没错，暴力并非我们种群的处事之道。我会自己了断的。”§!联络就这样被切断了。\n\n我方扫描器显示朔望号上的所有武器已经下线，整艘飞船的电力也渐渐切断，变得一片黑暗。当派出的搜查队伍登船时，发现船上并无任何生物，也早已找不到舰长了。但我们发现，最近有人进入了引擎舱，且有人取消了阻止进入能源核心的安保协议。"
ADD akx.9310.e:0 "Let's finish this, then."
CN2 akx.9310.e:0 "那么，就来做个了断吧。"
ADD akx.9310.e.response:0 "§G"[mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] out."§!\n\nThe captain salutes - wincing as the movement tugs at an old wound - and closes the connection."
CN2 akx.9310.e.response:0 "§G“ [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 通话完毕。”§!\n\n舰长敬了个礼，但似乎扯到了没有治愈的伤疤，咧了咧嘴。联络被切断了。"
ADD akx.9310.e.materialistic:1 "Before you go: did you learn anything useful?"
CN2 akx.9310.e.materialistic:1 "喂，先别走……对于你去过的那个地方，你有什么发现吗？"
ADD akx.9310.e.materialistic.response:0 "The captain grins a scar-stretched grin.\n\n§G"I hoped you'd ask that. Sending data now. [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] out."§!"
CN2 akx.9310.e.materialistic.response:0 "舰长布满伤疤的脸上闪现了一丝稍过即逝的笑容。\n\n§G“就知道你会问这个。我这就把找到的信息传送过去。 [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 通话完毕。”§!"
ADD akx.9310.e.spiritual:0 "We'll remember you in our prayers."
CN2 akx.9310.e.spiritual:0 "我们会为你祈祷的。"
ADD akx.9310.e.spiritual.response:0 "§G"And I have one more prayer for you."§!\n\nThe Captain recites an oddly resonant palindromic prayer of twenty-seven words that will fascinate your theologians, and closes the connection."
CN2 akx.9310.e.spiritual.response:0 "§G“也请允许我为你们祈祷。”§!\n\n舰长念诵了一句十分悦耳的奇异回文型祷言，共有27字长，然后就切断了通话。你手下的神学家一定会对此十分感兴趣的。"
ADD akx.9310.e.militarist:0 "Captain. We'll meet in fire, and honor."
CN2 akx.9310.e.militarist:0 "舰长。我们就以战火与荣誉相见吧。"
ADD akx.9310.e.militarist.response:0 "The Captain salutes.\n\n§G"I hope there'll be some sort of monument."§!\n\nThe connection cuts out."
CN2 akx.9310.e.militarist.response:0 "舰长神采奕奕地敬了个礼。\n\n§G“以后可别忘了给我建个纪念碑。”§!\n\n通话就这样断了。"
ADD akx.9310.e.fanaticcollectivist:0 "Whatever's happened, this is not our way. Surrender. We'll help you."
CN2 akx.9310.e.fanaticcollectivist:0 "不管是怎么一回事，好斗都不是解决问题的途径。投降吧，我们会帮你的。问题的途径。投降吧，我们会帮你的。"
ADD akx.9310.e.fanaticcollectivist.response:0 "The Captain hesitates for a long time. It becomes apparent that the bridge of the "Syzygy" is empty: there are no other crew.\n\n§G"It's too late for me,"§! the other [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] says at last, §G"but you're right. This is not our way. I'll do what I must."§! They cut the transmission.\n\nSensors report that the Syzygy weapons are offline; the ship is powering down. Very soon, it goes dark. When our salvage team boards the ship, they find no living crea, and no sign of the captain. But the drive chamber has been accessed recently, and the safety protocols that prevent entry have been overridden."
CN2 akx.9310.e.fanaticcollectivist.response:0 "舰长犹豫着，沉默了很久。从显示屏上可以看出，朔望号上早已灰尘满积，破败不堪，没有其他生存者了。\n\n§G“对我来说已经太晚了，”§!沉默许久的另一位 [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 舰长终于开了口，§G“但你说的没错，这不是我们的处事之道。我会自己了断的。”§!联络就这样被切断了。\n\n我方扫描器显示朔望号上的所有武器已经下线，整艘飞船的电力也渐渐切断，变得一片黑暗。当派出的搜查队伍登船时，发现船上并无任何生物，也早已找不到舰长了。但我们发现，最近有人进入了引擎舱，且有人取消了阻止进入能源核心的安保协议。"
ADD akx.9310.f:0 "Traitor."
CN2 akx.9310.f:0 "叛徒。"
ADD akx.9310.f.tooltip:0 "Close channel."
CN2 akx.9310.f.tooltip:0 "中断通讯。"
ADD akx.9315.name:0 "A Rendezvous: How it Ends"
CN2 akx.9315.name:0 "太空密会：结局"
ADD akx.9315.desc:0 "The "Syzygy" is powering weapons."
CN2 akx.9315.desc:0 "朔望号正在启动武器。"
ADD akx.9315.a:0 "If only there had been another way..."
CN2 akx.9315.a:0 "要是有别的办法就好了……"
ADD akx.9315.b:0 "So be it."
CN2 akx.9315.b:0 "那就这样吧。"
ADD akx.9319.name:0 "A Rendezvous: Interference"
CN2 akx.9319.name:0 "太空密会：干扰"
ADD akx.9319.desc:0 "A static-speckled message comes in from the captain of the "Syzygy", in [syzygy_location.GetStarName]. Behind them, the bridge is wreathed in smoke. §G"Too late,"§! they cough. §G"You left it too long. The Loop won't forgive me. Please -"§!\n\nThe message ends there."
CN2 akx.9319.desc:0 "收到了充满杂音的通讯信息，来自位于 [syzygy_location.GetStarName] 的朔望号舰长。画面上的驾驶室充满了浓烟。§G“太晚了。”§!舰长剧烈地咳嗽着。§G“你浪费了太多时间，时之循环是不会原谅我的。你一定要——”§!\n\n信息就这样结束了。"
ADD akx.9319.a:0 "Who did this?"
CN2 akx.9319.a:0 "这是谁干的？"
ADD akx.9319.a.tooltip:0 "The "Syzygy" has been destroyed by another empire. If you reach the system before the debris dissipates, you might still find something."
CN2 akx.9319.a.tooltip:0 "朔望号被其他帝国消灭了。如果能在碎片散落之前到达其曾经的位置，或许可以找到些有用的东西。"
ADD akx.9320.name:0 "A Rendezvous: The Captain that Will Be"
CN2 akx.9320.name:0 "太空密会：未来的舰长"
ADD akx.9320.desc:0 "[mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] is silent in the days that follow. It is no small thing to order your own death. But in time, that silence becomes a determination, and an almost reckless confidence."
CN2 akx.9320.desc:0 " [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 此后沉默了好几天。预见自己的死亡并不是件轻松的事。但随着时间过去，那沉默也慢慢变成了决心，甚至可以说是成为了鲁莽的自信。"
ADD akx.9321.name:0 "A Rendezvous: The Captain that Will Be"
CN2 akx.9321.name:0 "太空密会：未来的舰长"
ADD akx.9321.desc:0 "[mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] is silent in the days that follow. It is no small thing to hear that you are already dead. But in time, that silence becomes a determination, and an almost reckless confidence."
CN2 akx.9321.desc:0 " [mirrored_syzygy_admiral.GetName] 此后沉默了好几天。听到自己的死讯并不是件容易接受的事。但随着时间过去，那沉默也慢慢变成了决心，甚至可以被称为是鲁莽的自信。"
ADD akx.9321.a:0 "Worrying."
CN2 akx.9321.a:0 "真是令人担忧。"
ADD akx.9321.b:0 "What was, will be; what will be, was."
CN2 akx.9321.b:0 "过去即是未来；未来将是过去。"
ADD akx.9330.name:0 "A Rendezvous: The Day and the Hour"
CN2 akx.9330.name:0 "太空密会：此时此刻"
ADD akx.9330.desc:0 "In the years that follow, there are reported sightings of admiral [From.GetName] across [Root.GetAdj] space and beyond. When a celebrated leader dies, this kind of thing is not unknown, of course; and they had become a kind of legend since the Syzygy Rendezvous. But we can't be sure."
CN2 akx.9330.desc:0 "在随后的几年中， [Root.GetAdj] 领空内外都出现了 [from.GetName] 出没的消息。如果这样的知名领袖真的死去的话，一定会有消息传到我们耳中的；而这位舰长自从朔望号事件以来，已经成为了毫无疑问的传奇。不过，我们还是无法彻底确认。"
ADD akx.9330.a:0 "We may never know."
CN2 akx.9330.a:0 "我们看来是永远也不会知道了。"
ADD akx.9330.b:0 "Oh, we can be sure."
CN2 akx.9330.b:0 "其实完全是可以确认的。"
ADD akx.9340.name:0 "A Rendezvous: Funeral Treasures"
CN2 akx.9340.name:0 "太空密会：珍贵遗产"
ADD akx.9340.desc:0 "The forensic analysis of the remnants we've recovered has uncovered oddities. All parts of the ship were constructed at the same time - using techniques that match our own methods of construction - but some components appear to be hundreds of years older than others. A power cell that we've recovered performs much better than it should.\n\nFurthermore... two analysts that were assigned to the project have recovered unexpectedly from chronic health problems - in one case, a possibly terminal condition. The team is at a loss to account for this."
CN2 akx.9340.desc:0 "我们对太空船遗骸进行分析时，我们发现了数个疑点。虽然飞船的所有部件都是运用我方的建造方式构建，且构建的时间也都一致，但有些部件看起来却比其它部件要古旧很多，大约有数百年之差。还有，我们发现的一个能源核，性能也比其原本的那个要高效许多。\n\n\n不仅如此……参与项目的两名分析师本来受慢性病困扰多年，在此次行动后却恢复了健康。其中一人更是本已经病入膏肓……我方科研队伍尚无法对这一现象进行解释。"
ADD akx.9400.name:0 "The Coils of God"
CN2 akx.9400.name:0 "圣者聚集"
ADD akx.9400.desc:0 "Our observation station on [coils_planet.GetName] reports the rise of an unusual minority religious-artistic movement, the Coils of God. Primitive mechanical clocks are considered holy, but ritually destroyed after a year's operation. The worm- and serpent-analogues of the planets are protected from harm. Time, the Coils-priests say, is a labyrinth. "What was, will be; what will be, was" they intone in their prayers."
CN2 akx.9400.desc:0 "处于 [coils_planet.GetName] 上的观测站传来报告，最近一个名为圣者聚集的少数派精神艺术运动正在兴起。传统的机械钟表被该信念追随者们供奉起来，但每过一年又被在仪式中摧毁。各种与长虫或蛇相似之物也都被当做不可伤害之物。聚神祭司们称时间为迷宫。“过去即未来，未来即过去。”他们的祷言之中经常会包括这句话。"
ADD akx.9400.a:0 "This sounds familiar. Suppress it as best we can."
CN2 akx.9400.a:0 "有点耳熟啊。尽全力将其压制。"
ADD akx.9400.b:0 "This sounds familiar. Observe it as closely as we can."
CN2 akx.9400.b:0 "有点耳熟啊。尽可能进行细致观察。"
ADD akx.9410.name:0 "The Coils of God: a Subtle Persecution"
CN2 akx.9410.name:0 "圣者聚集：隐秘消灭"
ADD akx.9410.desc:0 "We've convinced native rulers that the Coils of God cult on [coils_planet.GetName] is a threat. The Coils-priests have been discouraged, imprisoned, or, regrettably, incinerated. Pre-FTL species have access to a deep well of hatred and suspicion: there are times when that's very useful."
CN2 akx.9410.desc:0 "我们已经设法让 [coils_planet.GetName] 的当地帝国相信，圣者聚集乃是威胁当地安全的异教。祭司们已经被抓捕，严重者还进行了消灭。那些没有达到超光速科技水准的低级生物们总是十分容易被鼓动，他们的心中充满了恨意与怀疑。这一点有时候正好可以为我们所利用。"
ADD akx.9420.name:0 "The Coils of God: Deep Roots"
CN2 akx.9420.name:0 "圣者聚集：根深蒂固"
ADD akx.9420.desc:0 "We've convinced native rulers that the Coils of God cult on [coils_planet.GetName] is a threat. The Coils-priests have been discouraged, imprisoned, or, regrettably, incinerated. But the cult is tenacious, and our observers express concerns that it may just have gone underground."
CN2 akx.9420.desc:0 "我们已经设法让 [coils_planet.GetName] 的当地帝国相信，圣者聚集乃是威胁当地安全的异教。祭司们已经被抓捕，严重者还进行了消灭。然而，他们十分顽固，我方观察员怀疑它只是将所有活动转入了地下。"
ADD akx.9450.name:0 "The Coils of God: the Labyrinth Ceremonies"
CN2 akx.9450.name:0 "圣者聚集：迷宫仪式"
ADD akx.9450.desc:0 "The Coils of God cult on [coils_planet.GetName] has grown with unusual speed. It can be found in every city on the planet, and it's fostering a series of lengthy ceremonies conducted by citizens in every walk of life. The whole species has taken to them with unlikely enthusiasm. The rich adopt elaborate circular dances for their celebrations. The poor daub complex looping sigils on their doors. Even playground games are chants about the circular nature of time."
CN2 akx.9450.desc:0 "处于 [coils_planet.GetName] 上的圣者聚集发展得十分迅速，在星球上的每个城市中都能发现他们的踪迹，而各个行业与忠诚的民众们也都热心参与其十分冗长的各种信念仪式。整个星球都十分热情地接受了这个信仰，令人感到有些可疑。富人们雇佣舞者，整日进行环状舞蹈。穷人们就只能在门窗上涂画十分复杂的圆形标记。即使是在广场上游玩的孩子们，口中也总是咏唱着时间如环，轮回不止。"
ADD akx.9450.a:0 "This is unsettling. Intervene to shut it down, but subtly."
CN2 akx.9450.a:0 "太令人不安了。秘密进行净化，将其彻底消灭。"
ADD akx.9450.b:0 "This is serious. Use force to shut it down, whatever the risks."
CN2 akx.9450.b:0 "事态严重了。不惜一切代价，使用强制手段将其消灭。"
ADD akx.9450.c:0 "Fascinating! Send a team to study the rites- to participate, if possible."
CN2 akx.9450.c:0 "还真是有意思！快派人去研究这些仪式，如果可能的话，进行参与。"
ADD akx.9450.d:0 "Primitives do primitive things. Continue to observe."
CN2 akx.9450.d:0 "原始种群自然会有原始的行为。继续进行观察。"
ADD akx.9460.name:0 "The Coils of God: Ceremony's End"
CN2 akx.9460.name:0 "圣者聚集：仪式终焉"
ADD akx.9460.desc:0 "Our campaign of subversion has disrupted the Coils of God ceremonies on [coils_planet.GetName]. The nobility abandon their cult. The looping graffiti on walls fades. The young return to playground games about flirtation, murder and other healthy childhood pastimes. There is a rash of suicides among Coils-priests. If there was a crisis, perhaps it is past."
CN2 akx.9460.desc:0 "我们在 [coils_planet.GetName] 上进行了对圣者聚集的严厉打压。贵族们放弃了信仰，门窗上的圆形标记也被人清洗干净。即使是年轻人也不再咏唱宗教歌谣，而是回到了调情打闹架等小伙子们该干的活动上。祭司们大部分都自杀了。危机已经被消灭在萌芽之中。"
ADD akx.9460.a:0 ""The Loop never ends, but it is not always completed.""
CN2 akx.9460.a:0 "“时之循环永远不会终结，但并非每个循环都会圆满。”"
ADD akx.9460.b:0 "Well done, everyone. Stand down."
CN2 akx.9460.b:0 "大家干得好。警备解除。"
ADD akx.9465.name:0 "The Coils of God: News from Underground"
CN2 akx.9465.name:0 "圣者聚集：地下情报"
ADD akx.9465.desc:0 "Our campaign of subversion has disrupted the Coils of God ceremonies on [coils_planet.GetName] - but it only fires the Coils-priests' fervor. They meet in secret, now, in subterranean temples. The nobility no longer dance the labyrinth dances, but they still bear hidden tattoos of the Sign of the Worm. And chants of "what was, shall be" still echo in playgrounds."
CN2 akx.9465.desc:0 "我们在 [coils_planet.GetName] 上进行了对圣者聚集的镇压，但聚神祭司们却更加疯狂。他们现在在地底的神庙之中进行聚会。虽然贵族们已经不再进行环状舞蹈了，但他们身上却隐藏着时之虫的纹身。在广场之上，仍然能听到孩子们“过去即未来”的嬉闹之声。"
ADD akx.9465.a:0 ""The Loop never ends.""
CN2 akx.9465.a:0 "“时之循环，永不终结。”"
ADD akx.9465.b:0 "Continue to observe."
CN2 akx.9465.b:0 "继续观察。"
ADD akx.9470.name:0 "The Coils of God: the Blood of Priests"
CN2 akx.9470.name:0 "圣者聚集：祭司之血"
ADD akx.9470.desc:0 "Our operatives are merciless. They abduct or assassinate every Coils-priest they can find. They set demolition charges on houses bearing the mark of the Loop. [coils_planet.GetName] is alive with rumors that the Coils' blasphemy has aroused the wrath of a greater god. Before long, the natives are beating the Coils-priests to death without any assistance from our operatives. The observation team is horrified; but if there was a crisis, it has been averted."
CN2 akx.9470.desc:0 "我们的行动十分残酷。只要找到了祭司，就将其抓捕或发动暗杀；只要见到了有着时之循环标记的房屋，就将其炸毁。在 [coils_planet.GetName] 也因此兴起了这样的传言：聚集之圣不符天意，遭到了上天的惩戒。这之后不久，当地人只要见到祭司，就会将其就地打死，再也不需要我方的帮助了。这个转变令我们的观察队伍惊恐不已；但危机至少是被消灭于萌芽之中了。"
ADD akx.9470.a:0 ""The Loop never ends, but it is not always completed.""
CN2 akx.9470.a:0 "“时之循环永远不会终结，但并非每个循环都会圆满。”"
ADD akx.9470.b:0 "Well done, everyone. Stand down."
CN2 akx.9470.b:0 "大家干得好。警备解除。"
ADD akx.9480.name:0 "The Coils of God: Navigating the Labyrinth"
CN2 akx.9480.name:0 "圣者聚集：迷宫之途"
ADD akx.9480.desc:0 "Our ethnographers are fascinated by the complexity of the ceremonies. They hypothesize secret communication channels, steganographic prayer-encodings, or algorithmic underpinnings to the rituals. In fact, they're returning preliminary evidence of this last when their communications abruptly cease. In fact, all communication seems to have ceased, planet-wide. Reports from satellites and survey craft flyovers confirm: there is no activity on the planet at all. No vehicles moving on the road, no emissions or thermal signatures in population centers. No signs of life...\n\nAnd here's the final report. The entire [coils_planet.Owner.GetSpeciesName] population of the planet - including your ethnography team - is absent, with all the business of a sudden but not violent exit. Meals were left unfinished, pets unfed, the occasional house aflame from an unattended stove. Gravitational anomalies were recorded at the assumed time of departure. In almost every street, the looped chalk sigils of the Coils bear witness."
CN2 akx.9480.desc:0 "我方派出的民俗学家对聚集之圣仪式的复杂程度表现出了极大的兴趣。他们认为仪式中可能包含隐秘的通讯频道，高度加密的祷文，甚至是基于算法的语言。但正当他们传送初步证据时，突然与我们失联了。而且不止他们，似乎整个星球对外的联系都在同一时间突然中断了。我们的卫星与低空飞行用于观察的飞机可以确认：整个星球上根本没有任何活动迹象。路上没有行车，人口集中的地方也没有任何热能信号。也就是说，没有任何生命迹象……\n\n\n最终的报告显示：整个 [coils_planet.Owner.GetSpeciesName] 的所有人口，包括你的民俗学研究队伍，都已经不在了。他们的消失虽突然，但并没有任何战斗迹象。桌子上还留着未吃完的晚餐，宠物们嗷嗷待哺，还有因没关掉炉火而导致的房屋着火。在人们消失的时候，科研队伍记录下了引力的特异变化，但没有其它线索。现在街道上留下的也只有用粉笔勾勒的一个个复杂又诡异的聚集之圣标记……"
ADD akx.9480.a:0 ""The Loop never ends.""
CN2 akx.9480.a:0 "“时之循环，永不终结。”"
ADD akx.9480.a.tooltip:0 "A science ship vanishes, and a civilization along with it."
CN2 akx.9480.a.tooltip:0 "一艘科研船消失了，还带走了一整个文明。"
ADD akx.9480.b:0 "A difficult lesson."
CN2 akx.9480.b:0 "真是残酷的教训啊。"
ADD akx.9490.name:0 "The Coils of God: Empty Temples"
CN2 akx.9490.name:0 "圣者聚集：空荡庙宇"
ADD akx.9490.desc:0 "A report has come in from our observation team on [coils_planet.GetName]: the ceremonies of the Coils of God have ceased. In fact, activity across the planet seems to be at an all-time low. The report indicates that the team are going to follow up with low-altitude passes in a stealth survey craft over major population centers...\n\nThe follow-up report confirms: there is no activity on the planet at all. No vehicles moving on the road, no emissions or thermal signatures in population centers. No signs of life...\n\nAnd here's the final report. The entire [coils_planet.Owner.GetSpeciesName] population of the planet is absent, with all the business of a sudden but not violent exit: meals left unfinished, pets unfed, the occasional house fire. Gravitational anomalies were recorded at the assumed time of departure. In almost every street, the looped chalk sigils of the Coils bear witness."
CN2 akx.9490.desc:0 "我们派往 [coils_planet.GetName] 的观察队伍发来报告：圣者聚集的宗教活动已经完全停止了。更甚的是，整个行星上的各种活动也几乎不复存在。报告中同时提到，观察队伍想要对星球上的人口密集区域进行低空蛰伏观察……\n\n后继报告表明：在星球上没有发现任何活动。路上没有行车，人口集中的地方也没有任何热能信号。也就是说，没有任何生命迹象……\n\n最终的报告显示：整个 [coils_planet.Owner.GetSpeciesName] 的所有人口，都已经不在了。他们的消失虽然突然，但并没有任何好斗倾向。桌子上还留着未吃完的晚餐，宠物们嗷嗷待哺，还有因为没关掉炉火而导致的房屋着火。在人们消失的时候，科研队伍记录下了引力特异变化，但没有其它线索。现在街道上留下的也只有用粉笔勾勒的一个个复杂又诡异的聚集之圣标记……"
ADD akx.9490.a:0 ""The Loop never ends.""
CN2 akx.9490.a:0 "“时之循环，永不终结。”"
ADD akx.9490.a.tooltip:0 "A civilization vanishes."
CN2 akx.9490.a.tooltip:0 "一个文明就此消失了。"
ADD akx.9490.b:0 "A difficult lesson."
CN2 akx.9490.b:0 "真是残酷的教训啊。"
ADD akx.9500.name:0 "The Waiting World"
CN2 akx.9500.name:0 "时之星球"
ADD akx.9500.desc:1 "It appears this is not the first [Root.Owner.GetSpeciesAdj] settlement on this planet. A number of facilities and districts have been carefully moth-balled and, with a little restoration, will serve our new colony well. But all records have been erased. Possibly this was a smugglers' port, or a haven for political exiles."
CN2 akx.9500.desc:1 "看来这不是此行星上 [Root.Owner.GetSpeciesAdj] 的首个据点。相当数量的设施和城市区划被仔细地包装了起来，只需通过简单的修复，我们就可以让它们恢复运作。但是所有的历史记录均已被销毁，因此我们无法确定这里曾经是走私者的秘密港口，还是政治流亡者的基地。"
ADD akx.9500.a:1 "Excellent! Make arrangements to restore the facilities."
CN2 akx.9500.a:1 "太好了！马上安排修复这些设施。"
ADD akx.9500.b:1 "This is too good to be true. Demolish the districts."
CN2 akx.9500.b:1 "没那么简单，肯定有猫腻。马上摧毁掉这些城市区划。"
ADD akx.9500.b.tooltip:0 "This will cause unhappiness in the colony."
CN2 akx.9500.b.tooltip:0 "这会增加殖民地的不满度。"
ADD akx.9505.name:0 "The Waiting World: Demolition"
CN2 akx.9505.name:0 "时之星球：拆除"
ADD akx.9505.desc:1 "Our engineers set charges and retire to a safe distance. The sites are reduced to ruins. Eventually, the ruins will crack and crumble to boulders, pebbles, dust, under the assault of wind, roots, rain. But their shell will endure for centuries yet; and there will be stories, we'll hear, of shadows in the stone by day, blue lights by night. Our colonists will avoid them. They'll attract no visitors."
CN2 akx.9505.desc:1 "我们的工程师安装好炸药后就撤退到了安全距离外。目标场地被炸成了废墟。最终，这些废墟也会在风吹雨淋等自然之力下开始崩溃成瓦砾和尘埃。不过它们留下的遗迹依然存在着；而我们的殖民者也在往后的日子看见遗迹处在白天时出现影子，夜晚时出现奇怪的声音。殖民者们都识趣地绕开该地点。"
ADD akx.9505.a:0 "Everything ends."
CN2 akx.9505.a:0 "一切都结束了。"
ADD akx.9505.a.tooltip:1 "The old facilities are demolished."
CN2 akx.9505.a.tooltip:1 "古代设施被摧毁了。"
ADD akx.9505.b:0 "Nothing is forgotten."
CN2 akx.9505.b:0 "世界是不会忘记的。"
ADD akx.9505.c:0 "I love those boomy noises."
CN2 akx.9505.c:0 "我最喜欢这种轰隆隆的声音了。"
ADD akx.9510.name:0 "The Waiting World: Shadows in the Walls"
CN2 akx.9510.name:0 "时之星球：墙中影"
ADD akx.9510.desc:1 "Our settlers were initially happy to make use of the districts on [waiting_world.GetName]. Their existence jump-started the colony. But now they've grown nervous. There are rumors that the facilities may still have occupants, or active security systems, although no evidence of either has been found. Some colonists insist, enigmatically, that there are "shadows in the walls.""
CN2 akx.9510.desc:1 "我们的殖民者很乐于利用[waiting_world.GetName]上的这些区划。它们能够让殖民地飞速发展。但是人们开始感到不安。传闻这些设施仍然有着使用者，或者是正在运行的安保措施。但是没有任何证据可证明这一点。部分殖民者甚至疑神疑鬼地坚持他们就是“墙壁中的影子”。"
ADD akx.9510.a:1 "Discourage this superstition. The districts represent years of effort."
CN2 akx.9510.a:1 "压制这种迷信。这些区划可以减少数年的奋斗。"
ADD akx.9510.b:0 "Why take the risk? They're only buildings. Have them demolished."
CN2 akx.9510.b:0 "若有万一呢？只不过是些建筑而已。全部炸平好了。"
ADD akx.9510.b.tooltip:0 "This will cause unhappiness in the colony."
CN2 akx.9510.b.tooltip:0 "这会增加殖民地的不满度。"
ADD akx.9520.name:0 "The Waiting World: Too Many"
CN2 akx.9520.name:0 "时之星球：人数激增"
ADD akx.9520.desc:1 "Interesting news from [waiting_world.GetName], where we found those abandoned districts. A census shows too many settlers. Records on a new colony are always unreliable, but as far as we can tell they have authentic citizen IDs - and no-one on the world has suggested there are any mysterious strangers. But the birth rate must have been extraordinarily high, or we have unlicensed migration, or... something. Somehow, the population is higher than we might reasonably expect."
CN2 akx.9520.desc:1 "我们当初发现那些被遗弃的城市区划的 [waiting_world.GetName] 传来了新消息。我们的统计发现那里突然多出了很多殖民者。不过这可能只是统计出错，毕竟那些殖民者全都拥有合法的公民身份证，而且没有人汇报发现任何新来的陌生人。或许是因为那里的出生率超级高，或者是因为……其他的原因。无论如何，那里的人口增长远远超出我们的预期。"
ADD akx.9520.a:1 "Destroy those districts. We should have done it much sooner."
CN2 akx.9520.a:1 "摧毁那些城市区划。我们早该选择这么做了。"
ADD akx.9520.b:0 "Investigate as best we can; keep an eye on the situation."
CN2 akx.9520.b:0 "尽可能进行调查，随时跟踪事态发展。"
ADD akx.9525.name:0 "The Waiting World: And Still They Come"
CN2 akx.9525.name:0 "时之星球：势头不减"
ADD akx.9525.desc:1 "Another update from [waiting_world.GetName], where we found those abandoned facilities. The number of colonists continues to increase, and now we're finding irregularities in the records - family groups that shouldn't exist, birth dates that make no sense. There must be secret migration from a lost colony, or else some peculiar sabotage by the colonists."
CN2 akx.9525.desc:1 "当初发现那些被遗弃的城市区划的 [waiting_world.GetName] 再次传来新消息。当地殖民者的数量持续攀升，我们最近在记录中发现了很多异常的地方——本不该存在的家庭、完全解释不通的出生率等等。这要么是某个未知殖民地的居民偷偷迁徙到该地，要么是有殖民者故意破坏记录误导我们。"
ADD akx.9525.a:1 "Destroy those districts. We should have done it much sooner."
CN2 akx.9525.a:1 "摧毁那些城市区划。我们早该选择这么做了。"
ADD akx.9525.b:0 "Peculiar! But we can always use more citizens. Monitor and continue."
CN2 akx.9525.b:0 "真是奇怪！不过殖民地还是人越多越好。继续观察吧。"
ADD akx.9530.name:0 "The Waiting World: Exit"
CN2 akx.9530.name:0 "时之星球：消失"
ADD akx.9530.desc:0 "An abrupt and total communications blackout from [waiting_world.GetName]. We somehow had too many people there. Now, it appears, we have no-one at all. The entire population has simply vanished overnight. Have they left the world? Gone into hiding? Engaged in planet-wide genocide?"
CN2 akx.9530.desc:0 "我们突然与 [waiting_world.GetName] 完全失联了。本来过多的人数，现在却似乎连一个都不剩了。整个星球的居民仿佛在一夜之间便消失殆尽。他们是离开了星球，还是躲起来了？还是发生了某种行星规模的消灭事件？"
ADD akx.9530.a:0 "Send a team to investigate."
CN2 akx.9530.a:0 "派一支队伍去进行调查。"
ADD akx.9530.b:0 "Abandon and quarantine the world immediately."
CN2 akx.9530.b:0 "放弃该星球，并将其彻底封锁。"
ADD akx.9530.b.tooltip:0 "This will put the planet permanently beyond use."
CN2 akx.9530.b.tooltip:0 "这将使这颗星球永远无法使用。"
ADD akx.9535.name:0 "The Waiting World: the Quality of Light"
CN2 akx.9535.name:0 "时之星球：光辉"
ADD akx.9535.desc:0 "Our team reports that [waiting_world.GetName] is, indeed, empty - not only of colonists, but of any sign the colony was ever there. The buildings are gone, the satellites and orbital structures are gone, the atmosphere shows none of the footprints of technological civilization. In the words of the team, it's as if the entire planet has been reset.\n\nThey also report fluctuations in local solar radiation that are characteristic of pre-supernova stars - and a number of "luminosity events" on the surface where light somehow appears to be accumulated and released by prismatic functions of the atmosphere. This is valuable and peculiar data. But it doesn't clarify the fate of the colonists."
CN2 akx.9535.desc:0 "探索队伍在调查 [waiting_world.GetName] 后，发现上面的确空无一人。不仅如此，就连殖民地的任何痕迹也都消失了。无论是建筑，卫星或轨道设施都不见踪影，连大气层也没有显示出任何先进文明曾经存在过的迹象。用队员的原话说，就好像是整个星球被重置了一般。\n\n队员们在当地的部分区域发现了类似超新星爆炸前的辐射反应，同时在星球表面发现数起“光照事件”，似乎是大气层中的不同气体导致了类似棱镜的反应，在各处积累并释放光芒。对我们来说，这是十分少见珍贵的数据，但仍然无法依此断定殖民地到底发生了什么事。"
ADD akx.9540.name:0 "The Waiting World: Everyone Is"
CN2 akx.9540.name:0 "时之星球：人人自危"
ADD akx.9540.desc:0 "Further unlikely news from [waiting_world.GetName], where the population had been mysteriously increasing. Population numbers are now what we'd expect, but there has been some sort of information sabotage, or... or what, our administrators aren't really sure. None of the individuals on the planet exists in our records. Every original colonist is missing. It's as if they've all been replaced by complete strangers.\n\nAs against that, they all swear they're loyal citizens of [Root.Owner.GetName]. They're all productive and apparently sane. In all communications they deny all knowledge of any confusion, and insist there must be a mistake at our end."
CN2 akx.9540.desc:0 " [waiting_world.GetName] ，也就是那个人口神秘增加的星球，又传来了令人难以置信的消息。那里的人口数目现在倒是正常了，但信息数据似乎遭到了破坏……或者说是，出现了帝国人员无法理解的现象。星球上的所有人口都不在我们的殖民记录中。当初派出的那些殖民队伍人口已经一个都不剩了。就好像他们全部都被陌生人代替了一般。\n\n然而，现在星球上的每一个人都发誓说自己是 [Root.Owner.GetName] 的忠诚子民。每个人都勤奋工作，似乎精神方面也没有问题。在所有的通讯联系中，他们都表示对记录错误并不知情，并坚持说是我们这边出现了失误。"
ADD akx.9540.a:0 "Abandon the colony immediately, before this spreads any further."
CN2 akx.9540.a:0 "马上放弃殖民地，以防此现象进一步扩散。"
ADD akx.9540.a.tooltip:0 "This will grant independence to the colony."
CN2 akx.9540.a.tooltip:0 "此举将会使殖民地获得自立。"
ADD akx.9540.b:0 "Purge them, and permanently quarantine the planet."
CN2 akx.9540.b:0 "全部全部清除掉，并彻底隔离整个星球。"
ADD akx.9540.b.tooltip:0 "This will put the planet permanently beyond use, but gain you Influence."
CN2 akx.9540.b.tooltip:0 "将会使这颗星球永远无法使用，但你可以从中获得影响力。"
ADD akx.9540.c:0 "Send a team to investigate."
CN2 akx.9540.c:0 "派一支队伍去进行调查。"
ADD akx.9541.name:0 "The Waiting World: the Purge"
CN2 akx.9541.name:0 "时之星球：消灭"
ADD akx.9541.desc:0 "This may have been a terrible crime. Or it may have preserved our nation from something even worse. The population centers of [waiting_world.GetName] seethe beneath the energies of our weapons. When we are done, every building is glowing rubble; no living sapient remains."
CN2 akx.9541.desc:0 "或许这个行动是不可饶恕的罪过，但它也可能无形中拯救了我们的帝国，使我们免遭更加危险的境遇。 [waiting_world.GetName] 的人口聚集地在我们的武器下颤抖。消灭完毕后，所有的建筑都成了废墟，无人生还。"
ADD akx.9541.a:0 "Erase the records. In a hundred years, no one will know what we did."
CN2 akx.9541.a:0 "彻底抹除记录。再过一百年，就没人会知道我们的所作所为了。"
ADD akx.9541.b:0 "Tell everyone. Let them hate, so long as they fear."
CN2 akx.9541.b:0 "把这件事告诉所有人。有了恐惧的压制，仇恨又有什么可怕呢。"
ADD akx.9545.name:0 "The Waiting World: Everything and Nothing"
CN2 akx.9545.name:0 "时之星球：一切与虚无"
ADD akx.9545.desc:0 "Our team reports that the population of the planet are healthy, normal and apparently bewildered by all the fuss. There are some peculiarities, though. An unusual number of multiple births; a planet-wide idiosyncrasy where no-one has any regard for punctuality; and fluctuations in local solar radiation that are characteristic of pre-supernova stars. They also observe a number of "luminosity events" on the surface where light somehow appears to be accumulated and released by prismatic functions of the atmosphere. This is valuable and peculiar data. But it could be coincidental. If anything has happened to the colonists, it remains a mystery."
CN2 akx.9545.desc:0 "探索队伍表明星球上的民众都平安无事，对我们的行动十分不解。但殖民地中的确发现了某些奇怪的事件。比如大量的多胞胎事件，而且整个星球似乎都没有时间概念。还在当地的部分区域发现了类似超新星爆炸前的辐射反应，同时在星球表面发现数起“光照事件”，似乎是大气层中的不同气体导致了类似棱镜的反应，在各处积累与释放光芒。对我们来说，这是十分少见珍贵的数据。但殖民地是否真的发生了什么事情，我们仍然无法断定。"
ADD akx.9545.a:0 ""What will be, was.""
CN2 akx.9545.a:0 "“未来即是过去。”"
ADD akx.9545.b:0 "Colonists: colonists are odd."
CN2 akx.9545.b:0 "殖民者啊，本来就是群奇怪的家伙。"
ADD akx.9600.name:0 "The Retainer"
CN2 akx.9600.name:0 "助人为乐"
ADD akx.9600.desc:0 "Hello, hello. We welcome you back to [Root.GetStarName]. Oh, you're different ones, aren't you? There are so many of you. So like our Brief, and yet so different. We request your kind assistance: do you have resources for our project? The Loop will assist us, but it's difficult to reach. Expensive, you see."
CN2 akx.9600.desc:0 "你好，你好，欢迎你们再次来到 [Root.GetStarName] 。啊，原来你们不是同一个种群喔。你们这些低级种群实在太多，有些分不清。看起来和我们之前那些简单生物有点像，但又不太像。不如你们来帮帮忙吧。有没有我们可以用的资源？虽然时之循环会给予我们帮助，但仍然有些困难。主要还是我们资金不够呢。"
ADD akx.9600.a:0 "Your Brief?"
CN2 akx.9600.a:0 "简单生物？"
ADD akx.9600.a.response:0 "Yes; the ones that set us in motion. You would call them a "civilization," we suppose, but in candor we have always found that term a little pretentious. They're gone, oh, almost a quarter of a galactic year, now. We are very sorry: we made mistakes. We can recreate them, approximately, with the Loop's assistance, but we do need resources."
CN2 akx.9600.a.response:0 "也就是我们的起源啦。你们应该会把他们叫做一个“文明”吧。不过说实话，文明这个词还真是有些自命不凡呢。那些家伙早在四分之一个星际年前就已经消灭了。或许这里也有我们的不对。不过如果时之循环给予帮助的话，我们是可以重新制造这个文明的。但还是需要一些资源。"
ADD akx.9600.b:0 "The Loop?"
CN2 akx.9600.b:0 "时之循环？"
ADD akx.9600.b.response:0 "Yes. The Strange Loop; the temporal coil, the hungry one. It has mentioned you, we believe. Or one of you. You are very numerous. What was, will be, or so it assures us. It can restore our Brief, more or less."
CN2 akx.9600.b.response:0 "没错，那特异之环，那时之轮回，那吞噬一切之力。它似乎曾经提到过你。或许是你们中的一个，毕竟你们人多嘛。过去即是未来，它曾经这样向我们保证过。它或许能够复活我们的简单生物。"
ADD akx.9600.c:0 "Yes."
CN2 akx.9600.c:0 "好。"
ADD akx.9600.d:0 "No."
CN2 akx.9600.d:0 "不行。"
ADD akx.9600.d.response:0 "Oh, we understand, we understand. You have so little time left. Spend it well, I suppose. A cordial farewell to you."
CN2 akx.9600.d.response:0 "啊，可以理解，可以理解。你们所剩的时间太少，希望你们能好好利用吧。我们衷心祝愿你们一切顺利。永别了。"
ADD akx.9600.e:0 "Perhaps later."
CN2 akx.9600.e:0 "还是以后再说吧。"
ADD akx.9600.e.response:0 "That's what my Brief always said. Later. But their Later was always our Now. How we do miss them."
CN2 akx.9600.e.response:0 "那些简单生物也经常这么说。以后。他们的以后可就是我们的现在啊。真令人怀念。"
ADD akx.9610.name:0 "The Retainer, Again"
CN2 akx.9610.name:0 "助人为乐，第二回合"
ADD akx.9610.desc:0 "Yes? Which were you? We think we might recall you, but there has been so much flickering lately. Oh, is it you? Has your sun not burnt out yet? Oh! You've come to give us what we need to return the Brief?"
CN2 akx.9610.desc:0 "你好，你是哪位？好像有点印象，不过最近总是有些恍惚呢。啊，原来是你喔？你们的恒星还没熄灭吗？啊，原来你是来给我们送复活简单生物的资源了？"
ADD akx.9610.a:0 "Yes. Here it is."
CN2 akx.9610.a:0 "是的。请收下吧。"
ADD akx.9610.b:0 "No."
CN2 akx.9610.b:0 "不行。"
ADD akx.9610.b.response:0 "Of course not; you would hardly have been able to gather all that already. You've been out here what, one-millionth of a galactic year? Adorable. We wish you the best."
CN2 akx.9610.b.response:0 "就是嘛；你们不可能这么快就把东西都集齐的。你们才在这里存在了多久，百万分之一星际年？还是太嫩了嘛。祝你们一切顺利吧。"
ADD akx.9610.c:0 "Perhaps later."
CN2 akx.9610.c:0 "还是以后再说吧。"
ADD akx.9610.c.response:0 "My Brief used to say that. "Later." But their Later was always our Now. How we do miss them."
CN2 akx.9610.c.response:0 "那些简单生物也经常这么说：“以后再说。”他们的以后就是我们的现在。令人怀念。"
ADD akx.9620.name:0 "The Retainer's Last Duty"
CN2 akx.9620.name:0 "助人为乐，最终回合"
ADD akx.9620.desc:0 "The technosphere absorbs the resources without thanks, and without any communication at all. It begins to radiate energy, brightly enough to be dangerous, and you withdraw. The black hole reacts. Space around it writhes and coils, in ways your archives match to the events of the Horizon Signal. The technosphere is blue-white now. Abruptly it flames and cools, and only slag remains.\n\nHave its Brief makers been restored? There is no trace of sapient life in the system. But sensors locate unusual hyperextremophile organisms in low orbit around the black hole, basking in its radiation. The Science Officer is certain they weren't there before. There is no evidence, though, that they're sapient. Perhaps they're some remote descendant of the technosphere's makers. Perhaps they're the makers' ancestors."
CN2 akx.9620.desc:0 "那圆球吸收了你们的资源，没有任何致谢，甚至可以说根本没有反应。但圆球突然开始发出光芒，似乎很危险的样子，于是你退至了安全距离。黑洞开始起了反应。其周围的空间扭曲萎缩，这和你之前记录的视界信号一致。圆球缓缓变成了亮蓝色，突然冒出火焰，又突然地冷却下来。剩余的只有燃尽的残渣。\n\n\n不知那些简单生物有没有被复活？星系之中仍然没有任何高等生物的存在迹象。但我们的扫描器在黑洞周围发现了超级嗜极生物，它们正在黑洞附近盘旋，似乎是在吸收其辐射能源。我们的科研专员确定之前并没有发现过这种生物。但没有证据显示它们是智慧生物。或许他们是圆球创造者的某种后裔，也可能是他们的祖先。"
ADD akx.9620.a:0 "Life eternal?"
CN2 akx.9620.a:0 "永生？"
ADD akx.10000.name:0 "The End in the Beginning"
CN2 akx.10000.name:0 "起点与终结"
ADD akx.10000.desc:0 "There is a consciousness outside time and beneath space. It is a labyrinthine tangle of desire and desperation. Our remote ancestors knew it as the Loop, the Worm-in-Waiting. We have met it out there, where the void is tormented by gravity. It seems to have taken a personal interest in us. There are mathematical proofs that it loves us, but love to the Worm is not like love to anything that subsists in ordinary space.\n\nWith all we have learned, we think that we might be able to use the Omega Alignment to open an access route - an Entry Point - for the Worm to manifest in our home system. (The Worm is fond of beginnings, and this is ours.) What consequences would that have? We have yet to find anyone who's prepared to commit to an answer. Immortality, perhaps, or apocalypse. But we would certainly learn a great deal."
CN2 akx.10000.desc:0 "在时间与空间的束缚之外，有着某种意识的存在。这个存在乃是渴求与绝望的迷宫。我们的远祖称其为时之循环，又称潜时之虫。我们在重力撕碎空间的地方见过这种存在。它似乎对我们产生了独特的兴趣。我们能用数学证明，时之虫是深爱着我们的，但它对于爱的理解或许与我们对爱的理解大不相同。\n\n根据我们的理解，或许可以运用欧米茄阵列打开一个入口，让时之虫进入我们的母星系。（时之虫最喜爱起点，而这里就是我们的起点。）会有怎样的后果呢？现在还没有人敢下断言。或许是永生，或许是灭亡。但在这个过程之中我们一定会学到很多。"
ADD akx.10000.a:0 "Perhaps the Worm loves us, and perhaps we could love the Worm."
CN2 akx.10000.a:0 "或许时之虫深爱着我们，而我们也可以报答它的爱。"
ADD akx.10000.b:0 "This is not a safe experiment. But we could learn so much."
CN2 akx.10000.b:0 "这实验并不安全，但我们可以从中学到很多东西啊。"
ADD akx.10010.name:0 "The Heart of the Sun"
CN2 akx.10010.name:0 "太阳中心"
ADD akx.10010.desc:0 "The Project is complete. The accelerators are online. The power network of a dozen cities is diverted to wake the pseudo-singularity at the heart of the Alignment. Space shudders like wind-wracked cloth. [Root.GetStarName], for a heart-stopping moment, dims, and then brightens. A shadow coils in its heart. The Worm is here. It unfolds like origami.\n\nAcross the system, sensors shut down in abject disbelief as the incomprehensible data of its arrival sleets through them. On the homeworld, our subjects scream and cower as they feel its attention turned up on them, and upon us. It presents a wordless question - or rather, we have become aware that this question was always what it was asking us, every time we encountered it."
CN2 akx.10010.desc:0 "项目完成了。加速器已经全部开启。足够供给好几个城市使用的电力供应已经接入，以唤醒阵列中心的伪奇点。空间如同风中破帆般抖动不停。在如同心脏停跳的一瞬间， [Root.GetStarName] 黯淡了下去，然后又重新亮起。在其中心可以观测到一团阴影的存在。时之虫到来了。如同逐渐铺陈开来的折纸一般，慢慢地展现着自己。\n\n\n随着时之虫的到来，星系中的各个传感器都检测到了大量无法理解的数据，接着全部失效。我们在母星上的民众哭喊匍匐着，人人都能感到那未知的生物正在注视着我们。它向我们提出了一个无言的问题——或者说，我们意识到了一个它已经问过我们无数次的问题，一个我们每次相遇都会问的问题。"
ADD akx.10010.a:0 "YES. Whatever it requires, we consent."
CN2 akx.10010.a:0 "好。不管它需要什么，我们都答应。"
ADD akx.10010.b:0 "NO. We have brought it here to learn and, if need be, defeat it."
CN2 akx.10010.b:0 "不行。我们把它引来是为了科学研究。如果有必要，就干掉它。"
ADD akx.10020.name:0 "The Future"
CN2 akx.10020.name:0 "时之未来"
ADD akx.10020.desc:0 "The Worm loves us. It will always love us, and thus it always has. It winds around the hot heart of our home star. It winds around every infinitesimal loop of genetic information. It provokes a shuddering series of cataclysms in the planetary crust of our home, but when our star grows cold, that cataclysm will warm us. We understand so much more. We will always be what we were going to be, wound tight in the love of the Worm."
CN2 akx.10020.desc:0 "时之虫深爱着我们。在无限的未来之中它深爱着我们，因此在无限的过去之中它也一直深爱着我们。它紧紧地缠绕着我们母星的核心，紧紧地缠绕着每一丝一缕无限循环着的基因信息。它在母星的地表造成一系列撼动世界的灾难，但每当母星的核心逐渐变冷，这些灾难又会将其重新唤醒。我们对世界的理解加深了许多。我们将会永远这样存在着，存在于时之虫的爱之中。"
ADD akx.10020.a:0 "WHAT WAS SHALL BE WHAT SHALL BE WAS"
CN2 akx.10020.a:0 "过 去 即 未 来 即 过 去"
ADD akx.10021.name:0 "The Shattered Loop"
CN2 akx.10021.name:0 "破碎的循环"
ADD akx.10021.desc:0 "The Worm came in through the boundary fences of spacetime like a hungry predator, or a jilted and furious lover. It's still out there, and wherever it is, no doubt it's angry. But you have the incandescent shards of its avatar to hoard and to study, as a cosmic trophy. Other empires will know what you have achieved today."
CN2 akx.10021.desc:0 "时之虫如同饥饿的猛兽一般冲进了我们的时空之中，像个气急败坏的情人。它仍然存在于宇宙中的某处，一定是心怀怒气吧。但你们同时也获得了它的化身留下的白炽碎片，可以用来研究，也是难得的战利品。其他帝国也会知晓你今天的成就。"
ADD akx.10021.a:0 "There are none like us! And perhaps there never will be."
CN2 akx.10021.a:0 "从没有像我们这样的存在！也许以后也再不会有了。"
